{"title_page": "Bridgit Mendler", "text_new": "{{short description|American actress, singer, and songwriter}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Bridgit Mendler\n| image         = Bridgit Mendler 2013 (Straighten Crop).jpg\n| caption       = Mendler in May 2013\n| birth_name    = Bridgit Claire Mendler\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1992|12|18}}\n| birth_place   = [[Washington, D.C.]], U.S.\n| home_town     = [[Mill Valley, California]], U.S.\n| occupation    = {{flatlist|\n* Actress\n* singer\n* songwriter\n}}\n| years_active  = 2004\u2013present\n| alma_mater    = [[University of Southern California]]<br />[[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]<br />[[Harvard Law School|Harvard University]]\n| relatives     = [[Christine Blasey Ford]] (aunt)<ref name=aunt/>\n| spouse     = {{marriage|Griffin Cleverly|2019}}\n| module        = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background    = solo_singer\n| instrument    = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* guitar<ref name=mcall/>\n* keyboards<ref name=futumbra/>\n}}\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]\n* [[reggae fusion]]\n}}\n| label         = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]]\n* Black Box<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.blackbox.la/|title = Home - Black Box|access-date = November 28, 2016|work = Black Box LA|quote = Mendler is listed under 'Our Clients', where a list of artists signed to their label are listed}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Bridgit Claire Mendler''' (born December 18, 1992<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |title=Bridgit Mendler |work=Disney Channel |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029195726/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |archivedate=October 29, 2013}}</ref>) is an American actress, singer, and songwriter.<ref name=\"Bridgit Mendler Bio allmusic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/bridgit-mendler-mn0002397780|title=Bridgit Mendler Bio|first=Matt|last=Collar|publisher=[[AllMusic]]}}</ref> In 2004, she began her career in the animated Indian film ''[[The Legend of Buddha]]'', later starring in the films ''[[Alice Upside Down]]'' (2007), ''[[The Clique (film)|The Clique]]'' (2008), ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]'' (2009)  and ''[[Labor Pains]]'' (2009) as a teenager. In 2009, Mendler signed with [[Disney Channel]] and played [[List of Wizards of Waverly Place characters#Juliet van Heusen|Juliet van Heusen]] on ''[[Wizards of Waverly Place]]''. Following the positive reception to her character, she landed the role of [[Teddy Duncan]] on the Disney series ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'', which ran from April 2010 to February 2014. Mendler also starred in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Lemonade Mouth (film)|Lemonade Mouth]]'' in 2011. Subsequently, Mendler portrayed Candace in the [[NBC]] [[sitcom]] ''[[Undateable]]'' (2015\u20132016) and Ashley Willerman in the musical television series ''[[Nashville (2012 TV series)|Nashville]]'' (2017).\n\nMendler was featured on two singles released from the soundtrack of ''Lemonade Mouth'', with both charting on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. In 2012, Mendler released her debut studio album ''[[Hello My Name Is...]]''.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/> It went on to peak at number 30 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], with over 200,000 copies sold. The record spawned the [[lead single]] \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\" (2012), which was [[List of music recording certifications|certified]] Gold and Platinum in various countries. The follow-up single \"[[Hurricane (Bridgit Mendler song)|Hurricane]]\" (2013) did not achieve the same success. Mendler has links with several philanthropic projects and humanitarian causes. From 2010\u20132012, she served as ambassador to [[First Book]], a campaign to encourage reading and gives books to children in need, and ''Give With Target'', with [[Target Corporation]] to raise funds to reform schools in the United States.\n\n==Early life==\nMendler was born in [[Washington, D.C.]]. She is the daughter of Sandra Ford-Mendler and Charles Mendler, and she has a younger brother named Nicholas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kidzworld.com/article/25656-adam-hicks-and-bridgit-mendler-qanda# |title=Adam Hicks and Bridgit Mendler Q&A |publisher=Kidzworld.com |date=May 17, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> She moved with her family to [[Mill Valley, California]] at the age of eight.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sing365.com/music/lyric.nsf/Bridgit-Mendler-Biography/1A4C0D3D509D38A84825783100252F15 |title=Bridgit Mendler Biography |publisher=Sing365.com |date=December 18, 1992 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120804000552/http://www.sing365.com/music/lyric.nsf/Bridgit-Mendler-Biography/1A4C0D3D509D38A84825783100252F15 |archivedate=August 4, 2012  }}</ref> It was there where she first expressed interest in acting and began working in plays.<ref name=\"hr\">{{cite web|url=http://www.backstage.com/bso/news-and-features-features/a-star-is-born-1004031788.story?pn=2 |title=A star is born|work=backstage.com|accessdate=December 15, 2010}}</ref> When she was eight years old, Mendler began taking part in local roles in both dramatic and musical theatre, and became the youngest performer in the [[San Francisco Fringe Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |title=Bridgit Mendler \"Teddy Duncan\" |work=Disney Channel |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928175856/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |archivedate=September 28, 2013 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> When she was 11 years old, she hired an agent to help her get acting jobs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kiss951.cbslocal.com/2012/06/01/10-interesting-facts-about-disneys-bridgit-mendler/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119064009/http://kiss951.cbslocal.com/2012/06/01/10-interesting-facts-about-disneys-bridgit-mendler/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=January 19, 2013 |title=10 Interesting Facts About Disney's Bridgit Mendler \u00ab Kiss 95.1 \u2013 Charlotte's #1 Hit Music Station |publisher=Kiss951.cbslocal.com |date=June 1, 2012 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 }}</ref> Mendler is the niece of psychologist [[Christine Blasey Ford]].<ref name=aunt>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/20/politics/blasey-ford-family-statement/index.html|title=Ford's family issues statement of support|last=Cole|first=Devan|date=September 20, 2018|work=CNN|access-date=September 21, 2018|others=Contributions by Eli Watkins, Gloria Borger, and Kate Sullivan |quote=In the statement, which was posted to Twitter by Bridgit Mendler, who identified herself as Ford's niece, the family asks that Ford's decision to come forward \"be treated seriously and respectfully\" and that her and her family's privacy be respected as her allegations are investigated. Mendler is an American actress and singer, and starred on a Disney Channel show}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2004\u20132008: Career beginnings===\n[[File:Mendler 2007.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Mendler at ''[[Alice Upside Down]]'' premiere in 2007]]\nIn 2004, Mendler got her first acting role in the animated [[Cinema of India|Indian]] film ''[[The Legend of Buddha]]'', in which she portrayed Lucy. When she was 13 years old, she got an acting role as a guest star on the soap opera ''[[General Hospital]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=TV.com |url=http://www.tv.com/people/bridgit-mendler/ |title=Bridgit Mendler |publisher=TV.com |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> She portrayed the dream child of character [[Lulu Spencer]], in which the two have an argument on Mendler's character's birthday.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ducksters.com/biography/bridgit_mendler.php |title=Bridgit Mendler: Actress |publisher=Ducksters.com |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> The scene, lasting just under a minute, is later revealed to be a dream.<ref>{{cite web|author=Fanpop, Inc. |url=http://www.fanpop.com/clubs/bridgit-mendler/videos/8952659/title/bridgit-on-general-hospital |title=Bridgit on General Hospital \u2013 Bridgit Mendler video |publisher=Fanpop |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> That same year, Mendler was the voice of the character Thorn in the video game ''Bone: The Great Cow Race'', which was based on the [[Bone (comics)|Bone comic series]]. In 2007, Mendler made her film debut in the [[film adaption]] of the [[Alice series|''Alice'' series]], titled ''[[Alice Upside Down]]''. Mendler starred alongside [[Disney Channel]] actress [[Alyson Stoner]] and [[Lucas Grabeel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/s?ie=UTF8&keywords=Alice%20Upside%20Down&page=1&rh=i%3Advd%2Ck%3AAlice%20Upside%20Down%2Cp_lbr_actors_browse-bin%3ABridgit%20Mendler |title=Alice Upside Down \u2013 Bridgit Mendler: Movies & TV |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> Mendler portrayed the antagonistic role of Pamela,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotflick.net/movies/2008_Alice_Upside_Down/bridgit_mendler.html |title=Bridgit Mendler in Alice Upside Down |publisher=Hotflick.net |date=May 12, 2007 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> who is the rival of Stoner's character, Alice.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/alice_upside_down/ |title=Alice Upside Down |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/alice-upside-down/id373694290 |title=iTunes \u2013 Movies \u2013 Alice Upside Down |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> For the film's soundtrack, Mendler provided backing vocals on the song \"Free Spirit\", performed by Stoner.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Alice-Upside-Down-Soundtrack/dp/B001FX9Y9Y |title=Alice Upside Down Soundtrack: Various Artists: MP3 Downloads |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> Also in 2007 Mendler auditioned for ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'' for the role of Sonny Munroe, but [[Demi Lovato]] was chosen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/lemonade-mouth-star-bridgit-mendler-8322669.html?cat=40|title=Lemonade Mouth Star: Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Yahoo!|accessdate=December 14, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925105138/http://voices.yahoo.com/lemonade-mouth-star-bridgit-mendler-8322669.html?cat=40|archivedate=September 25, 2013}}</ref> In 2008, it was announced that Mendler would play the role of Kristen Gregory in the [[film adaption]] of the popular teen novel series ''[[The Clique (novel)|The Clique]] ''by Lisi Harrison. Mendler had the role of Kristen, a girl who attends OCD on a scholarship, and works hard to keep her good grades.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/s?ie=UTF8&keywords=The%20Clique%2C%20Michael%20Lembeck&page=1&rh=i%3Advd%2Ck%3AThe%20Clique\\c%20Michael%20Lembeck%2Cp_lbr_actors_browse-bin%3ABridgit%20Mendler |title=The Clique, Michael Lembeck&nbsp;\u2014 Bridgit Mendler: Movies & TV |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n\nShe also had begun working on a film with actress and singer [[Lindsay Lohan]] titled ''[[Labor Pains]]'', which kept being pushed back due to various conflicts and problems. Though initially slated for a theatrical release, the film did not receive one in the US and was instead released as a TV film on [[ABC Family]] in 2009. The film did, however, receive a theatrical release in countries such as Russia, Romania, Spain, the United Arab Emirates, Ecuador, and Mexico. The film drew 2.1 million viewers, a better-than-average prime-time audience for ABC Family, and per the network, was the week's top [[Cable television|cable]] film among coveted female demographic groups.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblo/b135139_did_lindsay_lohan_movie_bomb.html|title=Lindsay Lohan new movie|publisher=E! Online|date=December 18, 1992 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> She had a supporting role in the film ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shineon-media.com/2010/03/09/exclusive-bridgit-mendler-interview-disneymania-7-good-luck-charlie-more/ |title=Exclusive Bridgit Mendler Interview: DisneyMania 7, Good Luck Marly & More |publisher=Shine On Media |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132012: ''Good Luck Charlie'' and ''Lemonade Mouth''===\n[[File:Jason Dolley, Bridgit Mendler and Bradley Steven Perry 2010 (cropped)-2.jpg|thumb|left|[[Jason Dolley]], Mendler, and [[Bradley Steven Perry]] in October 2010]]\nIn 2009, Mendler became a recurring character in the [[Disney Channel]] series ''[[Wizards of Waverly Place]]''. Mendler portrayed the role of Juliet Van Heusen,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bridgitmendlermusic.com/releases/wizards_of_waverly_place |title=Bridgit Mendler |publisher=Bridgitmendlermusic.com |date=March 21, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130118122606/http://www.bridgitmendlermusic.com/releases/wizards_of_waverly_place |archivedate=January 18, 2013  }}</ref> a vampire who later forms a romance with [[David Henrie]]'s character Justin Russo. This lasts till the series finale.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/wizards-of-waverly-place/bridgit-mendler-bites-back-on-30041.aspx |title=Bridgit Mendler Bites Back on 'Wizards of Waverly Place' |publisher=Buddytv.com |date=July 15, 2009 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925165730/http://www.buddytv.com/articles/wizards-of-waverly-place/bridgit-mendler-bites-back-on-30041.aspx |archive-date=September 25, 2013 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> Mendler would go on to appear in eleven episodes total for the series, spanning from 2009 to 2012 when the series ended.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://teenstarfanclub.com/index.php?title=Bridgit_Mendler |title=Bridgit Mendler |publisher=Teen Star Fan Club |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926045958/http://teenstarfanclub.com/index.php?title=Bridgit_Mendler |archivedate=September 26, 2013  }}</ref> In 2010, Mendler became the star of the [[Disney Channel Original Series]] ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'', centering on a teenage girl who makes videos for her baby sister to watch as she gets older.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-eyes-teen-star-86502|title=Disney eyes another teen star|last=Bond|first=Paul|date=July 14, 2009|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=April 7, 2010}}{{subscription required}}<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.dapsmagic.com/disneynewsarticle.php?id=9942|title=Disney eyes another teen star|last=Bond|first=Paul|date=July 15, 2009|work=dapsmagic.com|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63627AIRs?url=http://www.dapsmagic.com/disneynewsarticle.php?id=9942|archivedate=November 10, 2011|url-status=dead}}<sup>'''(Copy of original)'''</sup></ref> The series premiered on April 4, 2010, and was met with a positive critical reception and viewership.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.variety.com/article/VR1118017313.html?categoryId=14&cs=1|title='Idol,' Fox top week in demos|last=Kissell|first=Rick|date=April 7, 2010|work=Variety |accessdate=April 15, 2010}}</ref> In the third season, Disney Channel announced that the series would feature a same-sex couple. This decision caused a protest from the conservative group \"[[American Family Association#One Million Moms/One Million Dads project|One Million Moms]]\" asking Disney Channel not to air the episode. One of Disney's spokespersons told TV Guide the episode was \"developed to be relevant to kids and families around the world and to reflect themes of diversity and inclusiveness.\" Disney aired the episode as planned. Other people including actors [[Miley Cyrus]] and [[Evan Rachel Wood]] expressed their support.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/03/one-million-moms-good-luck-charlie_n_4717515.html |title=One Million Moms Responds To Lesbian Couple On Disney Channel's 'Good Luck Charlie' |first=James |last=Nichols |date=February 3, 2014 |accessdate=June 5, 2014 |publisher=The Huffington Post}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, she starred as Olivia White, the lead role in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Lemonade Mouth (film)|Lemonade Mouth]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/assets/pr%5Chtml/lemonademouth_011811.html |title=Lemonade Mouth |work=Disney Channel |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170917170722/https://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/assets/pr/html/lemonademouth_011811.html |archivedate=September 17, 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wesely |first=Tommy |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/blog/teen-vogue-daily/2011/04/meet-the-girls-of-lemonade-mouth-bridgit-mendler.html |title=Meet The Girls of Lemonade Mouth: Bridgit Mendler: Teen Vogue Daily |publisher=TeenVogue.com |date=April 15, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> watched by 5.7 million viewers on its premiere night.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/04/18/friday-cable-ratings-historys-american-restoration-leads-demo-disneys-lemonade-mouth-tops-viewing-sanctuary-smackdown-and-more/89850|title=Friday Cable Ratings: History's ''American Restoration'' Leads Demo; Disney's ''Lemonade Mouth'' Tops Viewing + ''Sanctuary'', ''Smackdown'' and More|publisher=tvbythenumbers.com|date=April 15, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> Mendler performed numerous songs for the film's soundtrack, which was released on April 12, 2011 by [[Walt Disney Records]]. The first single released from the soundtrack, titled \"[[Somebody (Bridgit Mendler song)|Somebody]]\",<ref>{{cite web|last=Gallo |first=Phil |url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/record-labels/bridgit-mendler-signs-with-hollywood-records-1005106532.story# |title=Bridgit Mendler Signs with Hollywood Records |publisher=Billboard.biz |date=March 31, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> was released on March 4, and peaked at number 89 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart.<ref name=\"billboard1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/297431/bridgit+mendler/chart?f=379 |title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=July 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/297431/bridgit+mendler/chart?f=887 |title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=July 29, 2014}}</ref> The second single, \"[[Determinate (song)|Determinate]]\", charted in numerous other countries and peaked at number 51 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref name=\"billboard1\"/> In an interview with Kidzworld Media, Mendler confirmed that there will not be a sequel to ''Lemonade Mouth'', commenting: \"There\u2019s not [going to be a sequel to ''Lemonade Mouth''] unfortunately. We had such a great experience working on the movie, and they tried to figure something out for a sequel, but everyone at Disney felt like the movie had completed its story in the first movie. It was a great experience, and I loved working with the cast members and still see them frequently.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsckids.com/2012/05/bridget-mendler-lemonade-mouth-wont-make-a-sequel/ |title=Bridget Mendler \u2013 Lemonade Mouth Won't Make A Sequel |publisher=Bsckids.com |date=May 16, 2012 |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> In 2011, Mendler had the supporting role of Appoline in the straight to DVD film ''[[Beverly Hills Chihuahua 2]]''. Mendler recorded the song \"[[This Is My Paradise]]\" for the film, which was released as a promotional single on January 11, 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/this-is-my-paradise-single/id409885695|title=This is My Paradise \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler|publisher=iTunes|date=February 7, 2012|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref> with a music video directed by Alex Zamm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/20/bridgit-mendler-this-is-my-paradise-music-video/|title=Bridgit Mendler \"This Is My Paradise\" Music Video|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=February 7, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111009121630/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/20/bridgit-mendler-this-is-my-paradise-music-video/|archive-date=October 9, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn March 31, 2011, it was confirmed that Mendler had signed with [[Hollywood Records]], and had begun working on her debut album.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/record-labels/bridgit-mendler-signs-with-hollywood-records-1005106532.story#|title=Bridgit Mendler Signs with Hollywood Records|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.teen.com/bridgit-mendler-arrietty-video-interview/ |title=Bridgit Mendler Secret World of Arrietty Video Interview |website=Teen.com |date=February 17, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301222323/http://www.teen.com/bridgit-mendler-arrietty-video-interview/ |archive-date=March 1, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Also in 2011 Mendler also starred the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Good Luck Charlie, It's Christmas!]]'', which premiered on December 2, 2011.<ref name=premiere>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2011/GLC_DCOM_premiere_date.doc|title=\"Good Luck Charlie, It's Christmas!,\" A Disney Channel Original Movie Premieres Friday, December 2|format=[[Microsoft Word|DOC]]|author=Ashley Kline|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|date=October 24, 2011|accessdate=October 25, 2011}}</ref> The song \"[[I'm Gonna Run to You]]\" was co-written and performed by Mendler, and was also featured in the film and released as promotional single on November 12, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/im-gonna-run-to-you-single/id479832434|title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 I'm Gonna Run to You \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler|publisher=iTunes|date=February 7, 2012|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref> Mendler later co-wrote and sang the ''[[Disney's Friends for Change Games]]'' anthem called \"[[We Can Change the World]]\", released as her third promotional single on June 11, 2011.<ref name=\"Disney Channel Medianet\">{{cite web|url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2011/We_can_Change_the_World_release.doc|title=Premiere of Disney's Friends for Change Anthem \"We Can Change The World,\" Performed By Bridgit Mendler, Friday, June 10 on Disney Channel and Radio Disney|accessdate=June 9, 2011|work=Disney Channel|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060009/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2011/We_can_Change_the_World_release.doc|archivedate=September 21, 2013}}</ref> In 2012, she guest starred in the television series ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' as Callie Rogers, a homeless runaway teenager with a mysterious illness.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://modoration.com/2012/01/19/sneak-peek-bridgit-mendler-on-house-episode/|title=Sneak Peek: Bridgit Mendler on \"House\" Episode|accessdate=June 9, 2011|website=modoration.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125064243/http://modoration.com/2012/01/19/sneak-peek-bridgit-mendler-on-house-episode/|archivedate=January 25, 2012}}</ref> She also made a guest cameo in Canadian teen drama [[Degrassi: The Next Generation|Degrassi]] in the Season 11 episode \"Don't Panic (1)\" as Clare and Alli's friend Emily Quagmire, in their civics class; she can also be seen in the show's opening sequence sitting on Jake's red truck alongside Alli and Clare. She voiced the lead role of Arrietty in the American English dub of ''[[The Secret World of Arrietty]]'',<ref name=\"Arrietty\">{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-01-08/arriety-u.s-dub-lead-actress-bridgit-mendler-named |title=Arietty U.S. Dub's Lead Actress Bridgit Mendler Named |work=Anime News Network |date=January 8, 2011 |accessdate=March 2, 2011}}</ref> and she recorded a song \"[[The Secret World of Arrietty#Music|Summertime]]\" for the movie which was released as a promotional single on February 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/summertime-from-secret-world/id499014527|title=Summertime (from \"The Secret World of Arrietty\") \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler|publisher=iTunes|date=February 7, 2012|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132015: ''Hello My Name Is...'' and ''Undateable''===\n[[File:Mendler 043.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Mendler performing on [[Summer Tour (Bridgit Mendler)|Summer Tour]] in July 2013]]\nIn Summer 2012, Mendler confirmed that the title of her official debut single was \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", written by Mendler herself, [[Emanuel Kiriakou|Emanuel \"Eman\" Kiriakou]] and [[E. Kidd Bogart|Evan \"Kidd\" Bogart]]. The song was released for digital download on August 7 and for radio airplay on August 21, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/ready-or-not-single/id548403391|title=Music \u2013 Ready Or Not \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler \u2013 iTunes Canada|publisher=iTunes Store (CA). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref> \"Ready or Not\" peaked at 49 in the United States<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=bridgit mendler|chart=Hot 100}}|title=Billboard Hot 100|publisher=Billboard |date=September 8, 2012 |accessdate=September 13, 2012}}</ref> and 53 in Australia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/35761/chartifacts---wednesday-14th-november-2012|title=Chartifacts \u2013 Wednesday 14th November 2012|publisher=ARIA Charts|date=October 11, 2012|accessdate=September 13, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016010247/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/35761/chartifacts---wednesday-14th-november-2012|archivedate=October 16, 2013}}</ref> but at number seven in the United Kingdom and within the top twenty of the charts in Belgium, the Republic of Ireland and New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/bridget%20mendler/|title=UK Singles Chart \u2013 Bridgit Mendler|publisher=UK Charts|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl//showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bridgit+Mendler|title=Bridgit Mendler Ultratop Discografie|publisher=Ultratop.be/nl/|accessdate=February 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/22/2013-03-30/|title=Scottish Singles Chart \u2013 Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Official Charts|accessdate=April 15, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz |title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart &#124; The Official New Zealand Music Chart |publisher=Nztop40.co.nz |date=December 24, 2012 |accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2013&year=2013&week=14|title=Discography Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Irish-charts.com. Hung Medien|accessdate=April 24, 2011}}</ref> The song received platinum certification in the United States<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=bridgit+mendler&format=&go=Search&perPage=50|title=US certifications: BridgitMendler|publisher=Recording Industry Association of America|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> and Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?st=Ready+Or+Not&sa=Bridgit+Mendler&smt=0|title=Gold Platinum Database: BridgitMendler|publisher=Music Canada|accessdate=October 17, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203015348/http://www.musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?st=Ready+Or+Not&sa=Bridgit+Mendler&smt=0|archive-date=December 3, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> and Gold in Denmark,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.dk/?q=certificeringer&page=39|title=16/05-2013 \u2013 Certificeringer IFPI Denmark|publisher=IFPI Denmark|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> New Zealand<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/|title=Bridgit Mendler on New Zealand|publisher=nztop40.co.nz|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> and Norway.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.no/trofesoknad|title=Bridgit Mendler on Norway|publisher=IFPI|accessdate=October 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130324030519/http://ifpi.no/trofesoknad|archivedate=March 24, 2013}}</ref> Mendler ventured on her first headlining tour, [[Bridgit Mendler: Live in Concert]], supporting her first studio album. The tour primarily reached only North America and she played at state fairs, music festivals and Jingle Ball's concerts series.<ref name=wesllfargo>{{cite web|url=http://www.bandsintown.com/event/5818753|title=Bridgit Mendler live in Philadelphia, PA|publisher=Bands In Town|date=October 28, 2012|accessdate=January 1, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060242/http://www.bandsintown.com/event/5818753|archive-date=September 21, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Mendler's debut album, ''[[Hello My Name Is...]]'', was released on October 22 by [[Hollywood Records]] and all the songs were written by Mendler with collaborators, included 12 tracks in standard version and 15 in deluxe edition.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/480366/exclusive-disneys-bridgit-mendlers-debut-set-for-oct-22 |title=Latest Music News, Band, Artist, Musician & Music Video News |publisher=Billboard.com |date= |accessdate=August 20, 2012}}</ref> Mendler was also involved in its production.<ref name=ft13>{{cite web|url=http://febreteen.com.br/2013/09/bridgit-mendler-fala-sobre-seu-album-atuacao-e-colaboracoes-em-entrevista-confira/|title=Bridgit Mendler at Yapert interview| publisher=Febre Teen|date=August 7, 2012 |accessdate=August 26, 2012}}</ref> The album peaked at number 30 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=bridgit mendler|chart=Billboard 200}}|title=Billboard Chart History: Bridgit Mendler|work=Billboard|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref> and sold less than 200,000 copies in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vakseen.com/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Soundscan-Week-26-2013.pdf|title=Week 26-2013 SoundScan Chartpack|publisher=Vakseen|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\nInternationally \"Hello My Name Is ..\" debuted in a few countries as Poland, Australia, United Kingdom, France and Spain.<ref>{{cite web | title= Bridgit Mendlerr: Hello My Name Is... \u2013 Album Charts Week November 26, 2012| publisher=ZPAV| url=http://olis.onyx.pl/listy/index.asp?lang=en| accessdate=April 12, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/41701/chartifacts---tuesday-13th-august-2013?pos=7|title=Chartifacts \u2013 Tuesday 13th August 2013|publisher=ARIA Charts|date=October 11, 2012|accessdate=September 13, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060515/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/41701/chartifacts---tuesday-13th-august-2013?pos=7|archive-date=September 21, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://zobbel.de/cluk/130330cluk.txt|title=UK Charts \u2013 Hello My Name Is...|publisher=UK Charts|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Bridgit+Mendler&titel=Hello+My+Name+Is...+Bridgit+Mendler&cat=a|title=Bridgit Mendler discography \u2013 Spain Charts \u2013 Hello My Name Is...|work=Spanish Charts |publisher=Hung Medien |accessdate=December 5, 2009}}</ref> Mendler's vocals have been compared to [[Lily Allen]], [[Cher Lloyd]], [[Jessie J]] and [[Karmin]].<ref name=muchmusic>{{cite web|url=http://blog.muchmusic.com/bridgit-mendler-releases-new-song-hurricane-from-debut-album/|title=Bridgit Mendler releases new song Hurricane from debut album|publisher=Much Music|date=August 7, 2012|accessdate=August 26, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929014009/http://blog.muchmusic.com/bridgit-mendler-releases-new-song-hurricane-from-debut-album/|archivedate=September 29, 2012}}</ref> She released two promotional singles on the album: \"[[Forgot to Laugh]]\" and \"[[Top of the World (Bridgit Mendler song)|Top of the World]]\". On February 12, 2013, her second single, \"[[Hurricane (Bridgit Mendler song)|Hurricane]]\", was released for radio airplay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/cool-new-music|title=Top 40/Mainstream Spotlight Trax|publisher=Top 40 Mainstream|accessdate=September 27, 2012}}</ref> The song peaked at number 1 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles|Bubbling Under Hot 100]] in the United States. On April 2 Mendler released a remix single version<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/hurricane-remix-single/id624664127|title=Hurricane \u2013 Bridgit Mendler (UK)|publisher=iTunes Store (UK). Apple|accessdate=July 9, 2013}}</ref> and, on June 21, an EP remixed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/hurricane-remixes-ep/id661020986|title=Hurricane (Remixes) \u2013 EP \u2013 Bridgit Mendler (UK)|publisher=iTunes Store (UK). Apple|accessdate=July 9, 2013}}</ref> Also in June Mendler debuted her second tour, the [[Summer Tour (Bridgit Mendler)|Summer Tour]], reaching only the United States. In April 30 she released the [[extended play]] ''[[Live in London (Bridgit Mendler EP)|Live in London]]'', by [[Universal Music]], recorded at a special performance in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/live-in-london-mw0002521639|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Live in London|publisher=Allmusic|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.umusic.co.uk/artists/bridgit-mendler/discography/live-in-london|title=Our artists / Bridgit Mendler / Discography / Live In London|publisher=Universal Music|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921061031/http://www.umusic.co.uk/artists/bridgit-mendler/discography/live-in-london|archivedate=September 21, 2013}}</ref> It  on Mendler's [[VEVO]] On November 16, 2013 was premiered the music video for acoustic version of \"[[Top of the World (Bridgit Mendler song)|Top of the World]]\", directed by Matt Wyatt.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vevo.com/watch/bridgit-mendler/top-of-the-world-(acoustic)/USH5V1321961|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 \"Top of the World\" (Acoustic)|work=MTV|date=May 13, 2010|accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref>  She recorded it on her own, independent of [[Hollywood Records]], and filmed in [[Griffith Park]], in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dis411.net/2013/11/16/video-bridgit-mendlers-acoustic-of-top-of-the-world/|title=Video: Bridgit Mendler's Acoustic Of \"Top Of The World\"|publisher=Disney 411|date= |accessdate=March 29, 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Brent Morin, Bill Lawrence, Bridgit Mendler, Rick Glassman from NBC Undateable.jpg|left|thumb|Mendler with the cast of ''[[Undateable]]'']]\nOn June 28, 2014, Mendler began the second leg of her [[Summer Tour (Bridgit Mendler)|Summer Tour]], in [[Charlottetown]], Prince Edward Island, Canada.<ref>{{cite web |first=Doug |last=Gallant |url=http://www.theguardian.pe.ca/Living/Entertainment/2014-04-22/article-3697279/The-Killers-to-play-Charlottetown-July-12/1 |title=The Killers and Bridgit Mendler to play Charlottetown July 12 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=April 22, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304052247/http://www.theguardian.pe.ca/Living/Entertainment/2014-04-22/article-3697279/The-Killers-to-play-Charlottetown-July-12/1 |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On that date, she sang one of her new songs, \"Fly to You\",<ref>{{cite web |author=[[Tiger Beat]] Staff |url=http://www.bopandtigerbeat.com/2014/06/watch-bridgit-mendler-performs-new-song-fly-to-you/ |title=Watch: Bridgit Mendler Performs New Song, \"Fly to You\" |work=[[Tiger Beat|Bop and Tiger Beat]] |date=June 30, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923193817/http://www.bopandtigerbeat.com/2014/06/watch-bridgit-mendler-performs-new-song-fly-to-you/ |archive-date=September 23, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> about a relationship that was said to be on the rocks but worth fighting for.<ref>{{cite web |author=Nik the Web Chick |url=http://www.q102.com/onair/nik-the-web-chick-26705/bridgit-mendler-debuts-new-song-12515405/ |title=Bridgit Mendler Debuts New Song!! |work=[[WIOQ|Q102 FM]] |date=June 30, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924083434/http://www.q102.com/onair/nik-the-web-chick-26705/bridgit-mendler-debuts-new-song-12515405/ |archive-date=September 24, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On July 5, she performed another new song, \"Deeper Shade Of Us\", with [[disco]] influences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popline.me/?p=41447 |title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Deeper Shade Of Us |work=Popline |date=July 2014 |accessdate=June 1, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714125649/http://www.popline.me/?p=41447 |archivedate=July 14, 2014 }}</ref> On November 25, 2014, Mendler was announced as a member of the main cast of the [[NBC]] comedy series ''[[Undateable]]'' in season two.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/news/good-luck-charlies-bridgit-mendler-163542451.html |title=Good Luck Charlie's Bridgit Mendler Joins NBC's Undateable as New Regular |work=[[Yahoo!]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205182119/https://tv.yahoo.com/news/good-luck-charlies-bridgit-mendler-163542451.html |archivedate=December 5, 2014 }}</ref> She portrays the character Candace, an unlucky and undefeatably optimistic waitress, who becomes part of the main group.<ref>{{cite web |first=Michael |last=Ausiello |url=https://tvline.com/2014/11/25/bridgit-mendler-undateable-season-2-cast-nbc/|title=''Good Luck Charlie's'' Bridgit Mendler Joins NBC's ''Undateable'' as New Regular |work=[[TVLine]] |date=November 25, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> During the season, Candace and Justin, played by [[Brent Morin]], were dating.<ref>{{cite web |first=Rick |last=Porter  |url=http://www.zap2it.com/blogs/bridgit_mendler_undateable_season_2_secret_disney_weapon-2015-03 |title=Bridgit Mendler is 'Undateable' Season 2's secret Disney Weapon |work=[[Zap 2 It]] |date=March 17, 2015 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Steph |last=Grassullo |url=http://www.teen.com/2015/03/18/celebrities/bridgit-mendler-undateable-interview/ |title=Dating Dos & Don'ts, Plus More Secrets from ''Undateable''{{'}}s Bridgit Mendler |work=[[Teen Magazine]] |date=March 18, 2015|accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> After initial reports, it was confirmed on July 2, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpopular.pe/espectaculos/2015-07-02-bridgit-mendler-ha-sido-eliminada-de-hollywood-records|title=Bridgit Mendler ha sido eliminada de Hollywood Records|website=El Popular|date=July 2, 2015 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> that Mendler left [[Hollywood Records]] earlier in the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.josepvinaixa.com/blog/bridgit-mendler-second-album/|title=Bridgit Mendler second studio album and Leaving Hollywood Records|publisher=Ultimate Music|accessdate=June 23, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150705211527/http://www.josepvinaixa.com/blog/bridgit-mendler-second-album/|archivedate=July 5, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpopular.pe/espectaculos/2015-07-02-bridgit-mendler-ha-sido-eliminada-de-hollywood-records|title=Bridgit Mendler ha sido eliminada de Hollywood Records|publisher=El Popular|accessdate=June 23, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|title=Bridgit Mendler Recording New Album|publisher=The Vinyl Reocord|accessdate=June 23, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706022926/http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|archive-date=July 6, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2015, NBC renewed with Mendler for a third season that consisted entirely of live episodes, which premiered October 15 of that year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/05/08/the-night-shift-renewed-by-nbc-for-third-season/401461/|title='The Night Shift', 'Undateable' Renewed by NBC|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=May 8, 2015|accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> In the season Justin proposes to Candace during a [[Backstreet Boys]] show and she accepts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|title=Bridgit Mendler Recording New Album|website=The Vinyl Record|accessdate=June 23, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706022926/http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|archive-date=July 6, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> On November 13, 2015, minutes before air time, a decision was made to pre-empt the then-upcoming live program due to the [[November 2015 Paris attacks]].<ref>{{cite news |title='Undateable Live' cancels broadcasts due to Paris terror attacks|url=http://zap2it.com/2015/11/undateable-live-cancels-broadcasts-paris-terror-attacks/|accessdate=November 22, 2015|work=[[Zap2It]]|date=November 13, 2015}}</ref> The next week, the live episode references were made about the attack as a tribute.<ref>{{cite news|title='Undateable Live' returns to address Paris attack \u2013 then gets back to funny business|url=http://zap2it.com/2015/11/undateable-live-returns-paris-attack-funny-business/|accessdate=November 22, 2015|work=[[Zap2It]]|date=November 20, 2015}}</ref> Following the third season, it was announced that NBC had cancelled continuation of the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/telenovela-undateable-canceled-nbc-1201755300/|title='Telenovela' & 'Undateable' Canceled By NBC |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=May 13, 2016 |accessdate=May 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2016\u2013present: ''Nemesis'' and ''Merry Happy Whatever''===\nIn 2016, Mendler produced her second studio album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2013/08/15/bridgit-mendler-talks-working-on-next-albu/ |title=Bridgit Mendler Talks Working on Her Next Album |website=ryanseacrest.com |date=August 2013 |accessdate=January 1, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140730235103/http://www.ryanseacrest.com/2013/08/15/bridgit-mendler-talks-working-on-next-albu/ |archivedate=July 30, 2014 }}</ref><ref name=billboard2013>{{cite web |first=Gary |last=Graff |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5645350/bridgit-mendler-checks-in-on-touring-hurricane-single-next-album|title=Bridgit Mendler Checks In On Touring, 'Hurricane' Single & Next Album |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=August 9, 2013 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> Mendler discussed some of the producers and songwriters she was working with for the new album, including [[Mitch Allan]], [[Dan Book]], Alexei Misoul, Augie Ray, Beloryze, [[TMS (production team)|TMS]], [[Ina Wroldsen]], and [[Steve Mac]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Daniel |last=Pac\u00f4nio |url=http://febreteen.com.br/2013/11/bridgit-mendler-tera-ajuda-de-tres-compositores-para-novo-album/|title=Bridgit Mendler has help of three composers for new album! |website=Febre Teen |date=November 23, 2013 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Mohammed \"Hamada\" |last=Sherif |url=http://hamadamania.com/2014/02/07/bridgit-mendler-collaborates-with-tms-for-sophomore-album/ |title=Bridgit Mendler collaborates with TMS for sophomore album |website=Hamada Mania Music Blog |date=February 7, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> On August 4, 2016, Mendler announced the title of her new single, \"[[Atlantis (Bridgit Mendler song)|Atlantis]]\", featuring Kaiydo, which was released on August 26, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/atlantis-feat.-kaiydo-single/id1140618666|title = Atlantis (feat. Kaiydo) - Single by Bridgit Mendler on Apple Music|access-date = August 26, 2016|date = August 26, 2016|work = [[iTunes Store]] (US)}}</ref> The EP, ''[[Nemesis (EP)|Nemesis]]'', was released on November 18.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=Bridgit Mendler|user=BridgitMendler|number=782986855184601089|title=So excited to announce that my #Nemesis EP will be out on November 18th!!! \ud83c\udf89 Pre-order is available right now!!|date=October 3, 2016|accessdate=October 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/nemesis-ep/id1159543311|title=Nemesis \u2013 EP by Bridgit Mendler|work=iTunes Store|location=United States|accessdate=October 3, 2016|quote=Expected Release: Nov 18, 2016}}</ref> In October 2016 Mendler was cast as Ashley Willerman on the fifth season of the CMT television series ''[[Nashville (2012 TV series)|Nashville]]''.<ref name=\"V-Nashville2016\">{{cite web |first=Will|last=Thorne |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/bridgit-mendler-nashville-season-5-cmt-1201881986/ |title=TV News Roundup: Bridgit Mendler Cast in 'Nashville' Season 5 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=October 7, 2016 |accessdate=October 7, 2016}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"THR-Nashville2016\">{{cite web|first=Kate|last=Stanhope|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/nashville-bridgit-mendler-season-5-936288|title='Nashville' Enlists 'Undateable' Alum Bridgit Mendler for Recurring Role (Exclusive)|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=October 7, 2016|accessdate=March 2, 2017}}</ref> On February 3, 2017, Mendler announced her new single, \"Temperamental Love\" featuring Devont\u00e9e.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/02/09/bridgit-mendler-temperamental-love-devonte/ |title=The FADER: Bridgit Mendler Shares The Heart Wrenching \"Temperamental Love\" Featuring Devont\u00e9e|work=The Fader|date=February 10, 2017}}</ref> The music video was featured the Youtuber Jam in The Van.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/bridgitmendler/status/832665399606988800|title=Bridgit Mendler on Twitter|publisher=}}</ref> On February 10, Mendler was cast in lead role of the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] comedy television pilot ''Thin Ice'', created by [[Elizabeth Meriwether]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/bridgit-mendler-star-fox-comedy-new-girl-creator-974632|title=Bridgit Mendler to Star in Fox Comedy From 'New Girl' Creator|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2017/02/10/bridgit-mendler-cast-thin-ice-fox-comedy-pilot-antarctica/|title=Bridgit Mendler to Star in Fox's Antarctica-Set Comedy Pilot Thin Ice|work=[[TVLine]]|accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/thin-ice-cast-bridgit-mendler-isiah-whitlock-fox-1201975948/|title=Bridgit Mendler Lands Lead Role in Fox's 'Thin Ice' Comedy Pilot From Liz Meriwether|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref> but the network ultimately passed on the pilot in May.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/fox-pilots-dead-linda-from-hr-type-a-thin-ice-behind-enemy-lines-university-1202100550/|title=Fox Update: Network Passes On All Remaining Pilots|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 23, 2017|accessdate=May 25, 2017}}</ref> On August 25, 2017, Mendler released the third single from her upcoming album titled \"[[Diving (Bridgit Mendler song)|Diving]]\" with American group RKCB.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/diving-single/id1266505547|title='Diving' - Single by Bridgit Mendler on Apple Music|work=iTunes|date=August 25, 2017}}</ref> The official music video was released hours after the release of the song.\n\nShe appeared in the [[Netflix]] comedy film ''[[Father of the Year (film)|Father of the Year]]'' along with [[David Spade]], [[Joey Bragg]], [[Matt Shively]] and [[Jackie Sandler]], which was released July 20, 2018.<ref name=whodoy>{{cite web |first=Amanda|last=N'Duka |url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/david-spade-bridgit-mendler-who-do-you-think-would-win-netflix-1202082421/ |title=David Spade, Bridgit Mendler, Nat Faxon, & More Co-Star In 'Who Do You Think Would Win?' For Netflix |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=May 3, 2017 |access-date=May 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\nMendler appears{{when|date=February 2020}} in the eight-part Netflix comedy television series, ''[[Merry Happy Whatever]]'', along with [[Dennis Quaid]], [[Ashley Tisdale]], and her ''Undateable'' co-star [[Brent Morin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/merry-happy-whatever-bridgit-mendler-brent-morin-ashley-tisdale-adam-rose-hayes-macarthur-cast-netflix-series-dennis-quaid-1202580816/|title='Merry Happy Whatever': Bridgit Mendler, Brent Morin, Ashley Tisdale, Adam Rose & Hayes MacArthur Cast In Netflix Series|work=Deadline|accessdate=March 22, 2019|date=March 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\n[[File:Give With Target 0044.png|thumb|right|Mendler visiting a school in [[Baltimore, Maryland]], to donate $25,000 for Target's campaign in 2012]]\nIn 2010, Mendler became ambassador to [[First Book]], a campaign to encourage reading and gives books to children in need.<ref name=\"disneydreaming.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/02/bridgit-mendler-talks-to-radio-disney-about-her-charity/|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks To Radio Disney About Her Charity|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231143026/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/02/bridgit-mendler-talks-to-radio-disney-about-her-charity/|archive-date=December 31, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2011 it became part of [[Disney's Friends for Change]], a [[Prosocial behavior|pro-social]] \"[[Environmentalism|green]]\" initiative of charity for environmental issues encouraging fans to take action.<ref name=\"disneydreaming.com\"/> As campaign theme that year Mendler released a promotional single on June 11, \"[[We Can Change the World]]\", raising $250,000 for the Disney Worldwide Conservation Fund.<ref name=\"Disney Channel Medianet\"/> She also participated of the [[Disney's Friends for Change Games]], an Olympic-based televised games aired on the [[Disney Channel]], getting $125,000 donation to [[UNICEF]] as Yellow Team captain and also competing for $100,000. But her team lost to the [[World Wide Fund for Nature]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.orlandosentinel.com/disney-a-mom-and-the-mouse/tag/bridgit-mendler/|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130723023657/http://blogs.orlandosentinel.com/disney-a-mom-and-the-mouse/tag/bridgit-mendler/|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 23, 2013|title=Disney Friends for Change Games begin airing June 24 on Disney Channel|accessdate=June 9, 2011|publisher=Orlando Sentinel}}</ref> In 2012 Mendler won the honorary award [[Common Sense Media]] as ''Role Model of the Year'' for her work against bullying.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=http://tv.broadwayworld.com/article/Disney-Star-Bridgit-Mendler-Awarded-2012-Role-Model-of-the-Year-20120426 |title=Disney Star Bridgit Mendler Awarded 2012 'Role Model of the Year' |publisher=Tv.broadwayworld.com |date=April 26, 2012 |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> Mendler was the third young artist to win the award, which usually honors environmentalists and scholars.<ref name=\"common\">{{cite web|url=http://www.commonsensemedia.org/csma2012 |title=Awards \u2013 2012 |publisher=Common Sense Media |date= |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> She also attended the annual [[UNICEF]] acoustic concert in [[New York City|New York]] to raise donations for charity in January 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fanlala.com/news/bridgit-mendler-and-noah-guthrie-added-selena-gomez-unicef-concert|title=Bridgit Mendler and Noah Guthrie Added to Selena Gomez' UNICEF Concert|publisher=Fanlala|accessdate=July 8, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130111010740/http://www.fanlala.com/news/bridgit-mendler-and-noah-guthrie-added-selena-gomez-unicef-concert|archivedate=January 11, 2013}}</ref> In July 2012 Mendler became ambassador of the campaign ''Give With Target'' with [[Target Corporation]] to raise funds to reform schools in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/07/27/bridgit-mendler-give-with-target-campaign/|title=Bridgit Mendler Give With Target Campaign|publisher=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108200253/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/07/27/bridgit-mendler-give-with-target-campaign/|archive-date=November 8, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The campaign aims to get $1 billion by 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sweetyhigh.com/blog/karma/bridgit-mendler-joins-target-to-raise-1-billion-for-schools|title=Bridgit Mendler Joins Target to Raise $1 Billion for Schools!|publisher=Sweety High|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> To start the Target campaign, they invested $5 million and distributed $25,000 grants to 100 in-need schools for the school year.<ref name=target2012>{{cite web|url=http://pressroom.target.com/news/target-launches-5-million-campaign-236888|title=Target Launches $5 Million Campaign for Education|publisher=Target|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> Mendler said about the incentive: \u201cI\u2019m excited to partner with Target on their Give With Target campaign and celebrate the start of a new school year with kids across the country. It's so important for all kids to have everything they need for a successful school year\u201d.<ref name=target2012/> In August she got $5 million donated by [[The Walt Disney Company]] and more $2 million donated by people at [[Facebook]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://startingpoint.blogs.cnn.com/2012/08/23/disney-darling-bridgit-mendler-helps-kick-off-nationwide-give-with-target-campaign-for-schools-in-need/|title=Disney darling Bridgit Mendler helps kick off nationwide 'Give with Target' campaign for schools in need|publisher=CNN|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Give With Target 0041.png|thumb|left|Mendler with children-in-need in Baltimore, in 2012]]\nShe was featured in a March 2013 public campaign [[Seventeen (American magazine)|Delete Digital Drama]] with the [[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen Magazine]] to end [[cyberbullying]].<ref name=seventeen2012>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/features/delete-digital-drama-quotes-bridgit-mendler#slide-9 |title=Spread Love, Not Hate|publisher=Seventeen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> About the campaign she said \"Being bullied is something I experienced in school and it is not fun...I love working to end cyberbullying. People don't have to push back as much as they would in real life. People need to realize bullying has just as much of an impact online because words are so cutting and difficult to deal with\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/features/delete-digital-drama-quotes-bridgit-mendler#slide-7|title=Fighting Cyberbullying Comes From The Heart|publisher=Seventeen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/features/delete-digital-drama-quotes-bridgit-mendler#slide-8|title=Bullying Online Is Just As Bad As In Person|publisher=Seventeen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> In May 2013 Mendler traveled to the United Kingdom to fundraise for [[Comic Relief]], given the aim of making her laugh with their jokes for a \u00a31 donation. The campaign aimed to raising \u00a3100,000 and give families hope.<ref name=daily2013>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2293262/Bridgit-Mendler-romance-Good-Luck-Charlie-star-Shane-Harper.html|title=It makes it easier dating another actor... everyone loves us together!' Bridgit Mendler on her romance with Good Luck Charlie co-star Shane Harper|work=Daily Mail|accessdate=May 22, 2013|location=London|first=Sarah|last=Bull|date=March 14, 2013}}</ref> About this work, she said: 'I love supporting something that is so positive and fun for people to get involved in and where people can really do something to help out.\"<ref name=daily2013/> She also worked with [[Acuvue]] being a mentor to help Katie, a winner of the 2013 ''Acuvue 1-Day Contest'', get closer to her dream of making a difference.<ref name=teencharity>{{cite web|url=http://www.teen.com/videos/celebrity-interviews/bridgit-mendler-acuvue-1-day-contest-winner-video/|title=Bridgit Helps Aspiring Singer Reach Her '1-Day' Goal!|work=Teen Magazine|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019053714/http://www.teen.com/videos/celebrity-interviews/bridgit-mendler-acuvue-1-day-contest-winner-video/|archive-date=October 19, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> On October 8 Mendler hosted the event [[We Day]] of [[Free the Children|Free The Children Foundation]], a campaign that helps build schools for underprivileged children of Canadian and American cities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dis411.net/2013/10/08/photos-debby-ryan-bridgit-mendler-and-more-at-we-day-minnesota/|title=Debby Ryan, Bridgit Mendler And More At \"We Day\" Minnesota|work=Disney 411|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weday.com/files/2013/09/FINAL-We-Day-Minnesota-Talent-announcement-Sept-14.pdf|title=Carly Rae Jepsen, Bridgit Mendler and Demi Lovato announced to join headliners the Jonas Brothers and Mia Farrow at We Day Minnesota|work=We Day|accessdate=May 22, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202225728/http://www.weday.com/files/2013/09/FINAL-We-Day-Minnesota-Talent-announcement-Sept-14.pdf|archivedate=December 2, 2013}}</ref> Also for [[Free the Children|Free The Children Foundation]] she was godmother of We Create a Change to help needy children.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/10/08/free-the-children-idUSnPNCG93582+1e0+PRN20131008|title=The Jonas Brothers, Carly Rae Jepsen, Bridgit Mendler, Queen Noor of Jordan, Minnesota Vikings and Barbara Pierce Bush take the stage today for We Day Minnesota|work=Reuters|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn November 16, 2013, Mendler participated of the World Challenge Marathon for [[Save the Children|Save the Children Foundation]], a charity race to helps children with health problems.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.savethechildren.org/site/apps/nlnet/content2.aspx?c=8rKLIXMGIpI4E&b=6248025&ct=13371981&notoc=1|title=Bridgit Mendler Takes on Save the Children's World Marathon Challenge|work=Save the Children Foundation|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In March 2014, Mendler traveled to region of [[El Quich\u00e9]], [[Guatemala]] to participate in the other project of [[Save the Children]] that helps underprivileged children in developing countries.<ref name=save1>{{cite news|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/03/31/bridgit-mendler-is-back-home-from-her-save-the-children-trip-to-guatemala/|title=Bridgit Mendler Is Back Home From Her Save The Children Trip To Guatemala|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426215518/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/03/31/bridgit-mendler-is-back-home-from-her-save-the-children-trip-to-guatemala/|archive-date=April 26, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> On April 8, she released the ''Baby Sit In'', that asks for teens to help give parents a break and give babies a healthy start to their life. Mendler said \"It\u2019s an easy way for kids to help little ones everywhere get a healthy start and an opportunity to learn just by doing something they do most weekends anyway\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/04/10/bridgit-mendler-launches-baby-sit-in-campaign-for-save-the-children/|title=Bridgit Mendler Launches Baby Sit In Campaign For Save The Children|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426215103/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/04/10/bridgit-mendler-launches-baby-sit-in-campaign-for-save-the-children/|archive-date=April 26, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Mendler represented the institution during the charity congress ''Save the Children's annual Advocacy Summit'' in [[Washington, D.C.]].<ref name=savethechildren>{{cite news|url=http://www.savethechildren.org/site/apps/nlnet/content2.aspx?c=8rKLIXMGIpI4E&b=8943369&ct=13844087|title=Disney Star and Recording Artist Bridgit Mendler and Kids Across America Kick Off Save the Children's #BabySitIn Volunteer Campaign in Nation's Capital|work=Save the Children|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> Carolyn Miles, the Save the Children's president, thanked Mendler publicly for humanitarian work: \"We are thrilled to have Bridgit on board. Her passion for helping children truly came through when she met with families and kids during her visits to the remote communities in the deserts of California and Guatemala's western highlands\".<ref name=savethechildren/>\n\n==Personal life==\n\n===Relationships===\n[[File:Shane Harper PNE 032.png|thumb|right|Mendler performing with her then-boyfriend, [[Shane Harper]], in 2011]]\nOn March 27, 2012, [[Shane Harper]] said in an interview with ''Officially the Hottest'' that he was dating Mendler. Harper told the interviewer that they became friends early in ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' and began dating in May 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.m-magazine.com/posts/happy-3-year-anniversary-to-bridgit-mendler-shane-harper-38455|title=Happy 3 Year Anniversary to Bridgit Mendler & Shane Harper!|date=May 20, 2014|work=M Magazine|accessdate=November 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://officiallythehottest.com/exclusive-interview-with-shane-harper/|title=[EXCLUSIVE] Interview With Shane Harper|work=Officially the Hottest|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928010350/http://officiallythehottest.com/exclusive-interview-with-shane-harper|archive-date=September 28, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[Cambio (magazine)|Cambio]]'' in September 2012, Mendler stated that it took two years between her meeting Harper and beginning to date him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambio.com/2012/09/04/bridgit-mendler-and-shane-harper-dating-good-luck-charlie/|title=Bridgit Mendler and Shane Harper Dating: Bridgit Spills All in New Interview|work=Cambio|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In March 2013, Mendler said in an interview with the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' that the fact her boyfriend is also her on-screen boyfriend on ''Good Luck Charlie'' doesn't disturb the relationship: \"I think it makes it easier, especially when it's a person who you've worked with for a long time.\"<ref name=dailymailshane>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2293262/Bridgit-Mendler-romance-Good-Luck-Charlie-star-Shane-Harper.html|title=EXCLUSIVE: 'It makes it easier dating another actor... everyone loves us together!' Bridgit Mendler on her romance with Good Luck Charlie co-star Shane Harper|work=Daily Mail|accessdate=May 22, 2013|location=London|first=Sarah|last=Bull|date=March 14, 2013}}</ref> To ''Classicalite'', Mendler talked about dating Harper, and said it took time for them to begin something, because she needed time to think. She said, \"We knew each other for a while, were friends for a long time. I think everybody was very respectful about it and wanted to make sure that it wouldn't be weird.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classicalite.com/articles/6293/20140225/bridgit-mendler-talks-dating-shane-harper-good-luck-charlie-finale.htm|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks Dating Shane Harper After 'Good Luck Charlie' Finale and Mia Talerico Death Threats |work=Classicalite|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In November 2015, Mendler revealed that she had ended her relationship with Harper.\n\nIn October 2019, Bridgit announced via her Instagram that she had married her long-term boyfriend Griffin Cleverly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/celebrity-couples/news/a35393/disney-channels-cutest-couple-bridgit-mendler-and-shane-harper-have-broken-up/|title=Disney Channel's Cutest Couple, Bridgit Mendler and Shane Harper, Have Broken Up|author=Noelle Devoe|work=Seventeen|accessdate=November 7, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nMendler has a degree in [[Anthropology]] from the [[University of Southern California]] (USC) in Los Angeles, California.<ref name=degree1/><ref name=degree2/> In 2012 Mendler joined USC's [[anthropology]] class.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://raggedmag.com/school-of-thought-bridgit-mendler-shares-the-perfect-college-curriculum/|title=SCHOOL OF THOUGHT: BRIDGIT MENDLER SHARES THE PERFECT COLLEGE CURRICULUM|work=raggedmag|accessdate=November 14, 2015}}</ref><ref name=hercampus/> She decided to study art after two members of her band joined her at USC.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.recapo.com/live-with-kelly-ripa/live-with-kelly-music/kelly-michael-bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-performance/|title=Kelly & Michael: Bridgit Mendler \"Ready Or Not\" Performance|work=Recapo|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In an interview with Brian Mansfield of ''[[USA Today]]'', Mendler said: \"My plan right now is just to do one class at a time and see how that goes. I'm just going to study something that will be interesting and doable from the road and just take care of my general education courses for now. I want to know something outside of what I do.\"<ref name=usatodayinterview>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2012/11/30/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-on-the-verge/1731703/|title=On the Verge: Disney's Bridgit Mendler|work=USA Today|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In 2013, she chose anthropology<ref name=universitystar>{{cite web|url=https://star.txstate.edu/node/2231|title=Q&A with Bridgit Mendler, Disney Channel Star|work=University Star|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908073431/http://star.txstate.edu/node/2231|archive-date=September 8, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and studied [[Medieval art|Medieval Visual Culture]], and medical Anthropology.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/2013/8/27/allentown_fair_bridgit_mendler_hopes_good.htm|title=Allentown Fair: Bridgit Mendler hopes 'Good Luck' follows her through career|work=Hispanic Business|accessdate=May 22, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002064740/http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/2013/8/27/allentown_fair_bridgit_mendler_hopes_good.htm|archivedate=October 2, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/reviews/bridgit-mendler-talks-good-luck-charlie-series-finale|title=Power girl bridgit mendler on dealing with change, not knowing what's next|work=Seventeen|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> To the ''[[University Star]]'', Mendler said USC was important so that she doesn't have a formulaic career: \"I think seeing that college life and what that would've been like, it does make you wonder what sort of lifestyle that would be, but I'm really grateful for what I have, and I think it's cool that, because my career path is not as formulaic, I can kind of decide when I want to take time off to do certain things.\"<ref name=universitystar/> In 2016 she graduated as an [[Anthropology|anthropologist]].<ref name=degree1>{{cite web|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/bridgit-mendler-has-found-her-post-disney-voice|title=Bridgit Mendler Has Found Her Post-Disney Voice|work=Noisey|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=degree2>{{cite web|url=http://www.uberhavoc.com/female-disney-stars-all-grown-up-and-smoking-hot/13028/11/|title=18 Female Disney Stars All Grown Up And Smoking Hot|work=Uber Havoc|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> Mendler has doctorate plans,<ref name=usatoday/> inspired by her mother, doctor of [[public policy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mithun.com/about/leadership/sandy_mendler/|title=Sandy Mendler, AIA, LEED AP|work=Mithun|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141122133016/http://mithun.com/about/leadership/sandy_mendler/|archive-date=November 22, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, Mendler was announced as one of the 2017 [[MIT Media Lab|MIT Media Lab's]] Director's Fellows.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.media.mit.edu/posts/2017-directors-fellows/|title=Media Lab announces 2017 Director's Fellows|accessdate=May 8, 2019}}</ref> In May 2018, she announced on Twitter that she started a graduate program at [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology|MIT]] with a focus on improving social media: \"As an entertainer, for years I struggled with social media because I felt like there was a more loving and human way to connect with fans.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/bridgitmendler/status/991629087197286400|title=First, the reason why I'm taking this time out to study is very connected to how i feel about social media. As an entertainer, for years I struggled with social media because I felt like there was a more loving and human way to connect with fans. That is what I'm going to study|first=Bridgit|last=Mendler|website=Twitter.com|date=May 2, 2018}}</ref> In January 2019, Mendler indicated that she was enrolled in a class at [[Harvard Law School]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Jordyn |last=Tilchen |date=2019-01-25 |df=dmy |title=Congrats: Disney Channel Star Bridgit Mendler Is Headed to Harvard Law School |url=https://www.j-14.com/posts/disney-star-bridgit-mendler-is-going-to-harvard-law-school/|work=J-14|accessdate=April 17, 2019 }}</ref>\n\n===Public image===\nMendler was included [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard's]] \"21 Under 21: Music's Hottest Minors\" list in 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/475070/bridgit-mendler-21-under-21-2012|title=21 Under 21: Music's Hottest Minors 2012|publisher=Billboard|date=February 29, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012}}</ref> In 2013 she also appeared in the list of thirteen.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5720544/21-under-21-musics-hottest-minors-2013|title=21 Under 21: Music's Hottest Minors 2013|publisher=Billboard|date=February 29, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012}}</ref> She was also chosen as one of the ten hottest young female artists by ''[[Forbes|Forbes Woman]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.womenfitness.net/teenage_celebrities3.htm|title=Forbes Woman \u2013 Fitness Top Ten: Beauty & Fashion: 2012 Top 10 Most Beautiful Female Teenage Celebrities|publisher=Billboard|date=February 29, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Mendler was chosen as role model of the year by [[Common Sense Media]], a non-profit organization that honors innovative minds from the worlds of entertainment, public policy and technology and rewards mainly teachers, scientists and philanthropists.<ref name=\"common\"/> She was honored for her charity work in anti-bullying actions, improving the lives of families by providing a trustworthy role model and creating a positive impact in the world.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Mendler was the second youngest artist to win the award, after [[Miranda Cosgrove]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rbr.com/miranda-cosgrove-honored-by-common-sense/|title=Miranda Cosgrove honored by Common Sense|publisher=RBR|date=April 26, 2012 |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\n\n===Influences===\nMendler has cited [[Bob Dylan]] as her biggest musical influence.<ref name=huffington>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/taylor-trudon/bridgit-mendler-on-good-l_b_2867749.html|title=Bridgit Mendler On 'Good Luck Charlie,' Music, And The Craziest Thing A Fan Has Asked Her |publisher=Huffington Postn|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Taylor|last=Trudon}}</ref> To Ed Condran of [[Hartford Courant]] she said that: \"You look at what Bob Dylan and artists like him have done and you just can't help but be blown away. I'm just glad I have the opportunity to start with this and I just want to take it as far as I can\".<ref name=courant>{{cite news|url=http://www.courant.com/entertainment/music/hc-bridgit-mendler-20141029-story.html|title=After A Disney Launch, Bridgit Mendler Making Her Own Sounds|publisher=Hartford Courant|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Taylor|last=Trudon}}</ref> In an interview with [[Disney Channel (Netherlands & Flanders)|Disney Channel Netherlands]], she revealed that her favorite song was \"[[Don't Think Twice, It's All Right]]\" from Dylan's 1963 album ''[[The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan]]''.<ref name=dcNL>{{cite news|url=http://nl.disney.be/disney-channel/backstage/bridgit-mendler/interview#/videoId/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not|title=Bridgit Mendler kwam naar Europa en vertelde over haar muzikale leven|publisher=Disney Channel Netherlands|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Taylor|last=Trudon}}</ref> To Taylor Trudon of ''Huffington Post'' she said: \"He was the first musician I got into where I paid attention to songwriting. He has a way of writing songs that's really playful with lyrics, but at the same time he's saying something that people feel is important and that they relate to. He spoke for a whole generation.\".<ref name=huffington/> Also to Trudon, Mendler cited [[Etta James]], [[Elvis Presley]], [[B. B. King]], [[Lily Allen]], [[Ella Fitzgerald]] and [[Billie Holiday]], and talked about these artists: \"I love that they have soul in their voices. I think that's something important\".<ref name=huffington/> Other musical influences include [[Elvis Costello]],<ref name=DisneyUK>{{cite web|url=http://www.disney.co.uk/disney-channel/features/bridgit-mendler-musical-influences#/videoId/bridgit-mendler-talks-music|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks... Music|work=Disney Channel UK|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[The Delfonics]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a462301/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-single-review.html|title=Bridgit Mendler: 'Ready Or Not' \u2013 Single review|publisher=Digital Spy|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]]<ref name=asia>{{cite web|url=http://news.asiaone.com/news/showbiz/bridgit-mendler-disneys-feisty-big-sister?page=0%2C1|title=Bridgit Mendler, Disney's feisty big sister|publisher=Asiaone News|date=August 7, 2012 |accessdate=August 26, 2012}}</ref> and [[Van Morrison]].<ref name=newswithtags/> During an interview with [[Yahoo!]], in 2012, Mendler also commented that her first female influence was the [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] girl group [[Salt-N-Pepa]] and sang an impromptu a cappella rendition of the song \"[[Shoop (song)|Shoop]]\".<ref name=yahoo2012>{{cite web|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/the-new-now/disney-actress-and-singer-bridgit-mendler-inspired-by-bob-dylan-and-the-fugees-221919537.html|title=Disney Actress And Singer Bridgit Mendler Inspired By Bob Dylan And The Fugees|publisher=Yahoo|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref>\n\n{{multiple image\n| footer    = Mendler has cited [[Bob Dylan]] (left), [[Florence and the Machine]] (center) and [[Feist (singer)|Feist]] (right) as her musical influences.<ref name=usatoday/>\n\n| image1  = Bob Dylan in November 1963.jpg\n| alt1    =\n| width1  = 110\n\n| image2  = Florence and the Machine-01.jpg\n| alt2    =\n| width2  = 110\n\n| image3  = Leslie Feist performs live at the Showbox in Seattle.jpg\n| alt3    =\n| width3  = 125\n}}\nShe said [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] band [[Fugees]] had great influence in her music training and also the recording of the debut album and song \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", \"One of the writers was like \u2018Check out this Fugees song, \u2018Ready or Not\u2019. So we all listened to it and were like that would be kind of fun to do some sort of interpolation off of that song, which is what we did. I think it stands by itself as its own song but it still has that memorable quality of the Fugees song, which is fun. I think we were all really proud of it and hoping it will go far\".<ref name=popdirt>{{cite web|url=http://popdirt.com/bridgit-mendler-talks-fugees-influence-on-ready-or-not/122712/|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks Fugees Influence On 'Ready Or Not'|publisher=Pop Dirt|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> For her debut album, ''[[Hello My Name Is...]]'', Mendler was inspired by [[indie pop]] singers [[Ingrid Michaelson]] and [[Feist (singer)|Feist]].<ref name=chese>{{cite web |url=http://chestercountymoms.com/2013/08/bridgit-mendler-is-coming-to-the-keswick-theatre-on-august-29-2013.html|title=Bridgit Mendler is coming to the Keswick Theatre on August 29, 2013|date=May 2013 |publisher=Chester Country Moms|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> Among the [[pop music]] artists, she cited [[Maroon 5]],<ref name=grammyinterview/> [[No Doubt]], [[Destiny's Child]],<ref name=newswithtags>{{cite web|url=http://newswithtags.com/Bridgit%20Mendler/artistdirect-bridgit-mendler-talks-hello-my-name-is-summer-tour-and-more#.UdmPH6zW78I|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks \"Hello My Name Is...\", Summer Tour, and More|work=newswithtags.com/|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[Justin Timberlake]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/bridgit-mendler/377384-bridgit-mendler-one-direction-have-great-voices|title=EXCLUSIVE! We chat to the Disney star about 1D, JT and Britney|work=MTV|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[Beyonc\u00e9]] and [[Bruno Mars]].<ref name=huffington/>  She cited [[Jamie Foxx]] as a great model of how to have a career in acting and music.<ref name=huffington/>\n\nMendler said that is influenced by British [[Neo soul|neo-soul]] and listed [[Ellie Goulding]], [[Florence and the Machine]], [[Marina and the Diamonds|Marina Diamandis]], and [[Lianne La Havas]] as her biggest British influences.<ref name=usatoday>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2012/11/30/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-on-the-verge/1731703/|title=On the Verge: Disney's Bridgit Mendler|work=USA Today|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Brian|last=Mansfield}}</ref> She has mentioned [[Natasha Bedingfield]],<ref name=newswithtags/> [[Broken Bells]], [[Mark Ronson]] and [[Amy Winehouse]].<ref name=DisneyUK/> In 2013 Mendler revealed to have a big admiration for the [[Adele]]'s musical style. To [[Disney Channel (UK and Ireland)|Disney Channel UK]] she said that \"admire the career of Adele, because she has her own musical style. She does things her way and writes about things she is passionate about. It is really working out well for her\".<ref name=DisneyUK/> She was also influenced by Canadian artists [[Feist (singer)|Feist]]<ref name=grammyinterview>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/news/bridgit-mendler-performs-exclusive-set-at-the-recording-academy|title=Bridgit Mendler Performs Exclusive Set At The Recording Academy|work=Grammy|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> and [[Tegan and Sara]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dis411.net/2013/02/21/bridgit-mendlers-acoustic-version-of-i-was-a-fool/|title=Bridgit Mendler's Acoustic Version Of \"I Was A Fool\"|publisher=Dis411|accessdate=July 28, 2013}}</ref> To [[Hartford Courant]] she commented: \"I've been a fan of Tegan and Sara's for awhile. They just do what they want to do. They don't follow trends\".<ref name=courant/> She covered the song \"[[I Was a Fool]]\" by the duo and released with the message: \"I heard this song by Tegan and Sara a couple weeks ago and couldn't stop singing it, so I just had to do my own version\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fanpop.com/clubs/bridgit-mendler/videos/34787055/title/bridgit-mendler-fool-acoustic-cover|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 I Was A Fool (Acoustic Cover)|accessdate=July 28, 2013|publisher=Fanpop}}</ref> In 2014, she mentioned in an interview to [[CKQK-FM]] Canadian artists [[Nelly Furtado]], [[Joni Mitchell]] and European bands [[Coldplay]] and [[Little Dragon]] as influences in composing her second album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/hot1055fm/hot-1055-chats-with-bridgit-mendler|title=HOT 105.5 Chats with Bridgit Mendler|work=Hot 105, 5 FM by CKQK-FM|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn acting career, Mendler has cited some influences as [[Jamie Foxx]], [[Natalie Portman]] and [[Rachel McAdams]]. About McAdams she said that \"She plays a variety of roles, she has a lot of charisma, and she doesn\u2019t try to live her life in the public eye\".<ref name=hercampus>{{cite web|url=http://www.hercampus.com/school/george-mason/hc-interviews-bridgit-mendler|title=HC Interviews Bridgit Mendler|work=Her Campus|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> She also admires the dedication of [[Christian Bale]]: \"I could not live my life as committed to the craft as he does, with body transformations and such, he goes to such extremes but he is very admirable\".<ref name=hercampus/> Mendler also mentioned [[Lindsay Lohan]] as a great actress.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chroniquedisney.fr/dossier/2013-mendler.htm|title=Rencontre avec Bridgit Mendler|work=Chronique Disney|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Lyrical themes and songwriting===\n{{Quote box|width=30em|align=right|quote=I think the fear when writing a song always that the outside world won\u2019t think it\u2019s as awesome as you do. That\u2019s the scary part about progressing through releasing the song, and also the fun part in sharing it with other people. Sharing that experience with all of these people, it goes from being something that\u2019s very much for me and for the other writers who wrote with me, into being something that\u2019s for everybody else. That\u2019s what performing is. You\u2019re giving it to everyone else. I think that that\u2019s really cool, it\u2019s also super trippy, because you\u2019d never think this thing that you created in a small room with four other people would be something you\u2019d get to share with so many people\".|source=\u2014 Mendler about the writing process.<ref name=popdirt/>}}\n\nThematically, Guilherme Tintel of Portal It Pop has noted that Mendler wasn't immature as the first work of other [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]] artists.<ref name=portalitpop>{{cite web|url=http://www.portalitpop.com/2012/11/review-os-primeiros-passos-de-bridgit.html|title=Review: Os primeiros passos de Bridgit Mendler em \"Hello My Name Is...\"|publisher=Portal It Pop|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> Tintel compares her songs to [[Jessie J]], [[Katy Perry]], [[Natalia Kills]] and [[Taylor Swift]].<ref name=portalitpop/> Mendler said that the writing process isn't hard, because she was influenced by her own experiences.<ref name=popdirt/> Her debut single, \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", talks about self-confidence and deal with boys.<ref name=popdirt/> To Pop Dirt Mendler said: \"I consider myself to be that girl sitting at the curb waiting for the world, so I think it\u2019s a great message to send to just go for the things that you want to take charge of\".<ref name=popdirt/> Her debut album discussed relationships (\"Rocks at My Window\", \"Top of the World\", \"Love Will Tell Us Where to Go\", \"The Fall Song\" and \"Hold On for Dear Love\"), break-up (\"5:15\"), alienation and romantic chaos (\"Hurricane\" and \"Forgot to Laugh\"), self-confidence (\"Ready or Not\"), self-esteem (\"City Lights\"), friendship (\"We're Dancing\"), money (\"All I See Is Gold\") and blonde girls (\"Blonde\").<ref name=portalitpop/>\n\nTo [[Hartford Courant]] she commented that writing is a compulsion. \"It's also something I really enjoy. I like to create. It's part of being a recording artist. I love to write songs\".<ref name=courant/> Mendler also said she didn't want to make [[Mainstream|commercial songs]], but timeless songs. \"I want to make music that stands the test of time. You look at what [[Bob Dylan]] and artists like him have done and you just can't help but be blown away. I'm just glad I have the opportunity to start with this and I just want to take it as far as I can. I wanted variety and to just make things really interesting. This isn't just something that comes out of a machine. It came out of me. This isn't about product. I want to grow as an artist. I remember listening to certain recording artists and songs that had a really big impact on me\".<ref name=courant/>\n\n===Musical and voice style===\nMendler's vocal range spans 3.4 octaves.<ref name=ftvocal>{{cite web|url=http://febreteen.com.br/2013/11/vocal-pop-analise-vocal-bridgit-mendler/|title=VOCAL POP: An\u00e1lise Vocal Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Febre Teen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref><ref name=vocalpop>{{cite web|url=http://www.vocalpop.com.br/2013/09/analise-vocal-bridgit-mendler_6.html|title=Vocal: Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Vocal Pop Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503215540/http://www.vocalpop.com.br/2013/09/analise-vocal-bridgit-mendler_6.html|archive-date=May 3, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> She's a [[mezzo-soprano]].<ref name=ftvocal/> She plays [[guitar]],<ref name=mcall>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.mcall.com/lehighvalleymusic/2013/08/bridgit-mendler-sees-end-of-disneys-good-luck-charlie-as-opportunity-for-her-music-to-flourish.html|title=Speaking with Bridgit Mendler: Star of Disney's 'Good Luck Charlie' sees show's end as opportunity for her music to flourish|publisher=M.Call|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> [[keyboard instrument|keyboard]],<ref name=futumbra>{{cite web|url=http://futumbra.com/bridgit_mendler/7|title=Bridgit Mendler plays the keyboard while performing \"Song for You\"|publisher=Futumbra|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005003703/http://futumbra.com/bridgit_mendler/7|archive-date=October 5, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> and [[keytar]]<ref name=mmag>{{cite web|url=http://www.m-magazine.com/posts/bridgit-mendler-rocks-out-on-the-keytar-15883|title=BRIDGIT MENDLER ROCKS OUT ON THE KEYTAR!|publisher=M-Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> S\u00e1vio Alves of Febre Teen Magazine said that Mendler's voice was \"strong and sweet\". He calls Mendler's voice as having a \"metallic tone\" and this being \"rare in young female singers\".<ref name=ftvocal/> His voice was compared to [[Indie pop|indie]] and [[blues]] artists.<ref name=vocalpop/> Her music is generally [[Pop music|pop]]<ref name=\"Bridgit Mendler Bio allmusic\"/> and [[reggae fusion]]<ref name=rickey1>{{cite web|url=http://www.rickey.org/bridgit-mendler-r|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Hello My Name Is\u2026 \u2013 Album Review|publisher=Rickey|date=October 28, 2012|accessdate=January 1, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130415172741/http://www.rickey.org/bridgit-mendler-r|archivedate=April 15, 2013}}</ref><ref name=muchmusic/> and has features of [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]],<ref name=\"Noisey\">{{cite web|url = https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/premiere-bridgit-mendler-do-you-miss-me-at-all|title = PREMIERE: Bridgit Mendler - 'Do You Miss Me at All' - Noisey|author = Kim Taylor Bennett|access-date = November 4, 2016|date = November 3, 2016|work = [[Vice (magazine)|Noisey]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Bridgit Mendler Bio allmusic\"/><ref name=\"muchmusic\"/> [[funk]],<ref name=gossiplife>{{cite web|url=http://thismoment.gossipfile.com/2012/09/23/bridgit-mendler-hurricane-listen-now/|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 'Hurricane' LISTEN NOW|publisher=Gossip File|date=August 7, 2012|accessdate=August 26, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130216042831/http://thismoment.gossipfile.com/2012/09/23/bridgit-mendler-hurricane-listen-now/|archivedate=February 16, 2013}}</ref> and [[hip hop soul]].<ref name=asia/> In an interview, she said she prefers to escape the traditional [[Pop music|pop]] and [[dance-pop]] and adding other elements. \"I have [[funk]]y, [[R&B]] tendencies when I write by myself. I really love [[doo-wop]] and a [[jazz]]y swing beat. Rhythm is a big emphasis in my own writing\".<ref name=chese/> Her voice and style has been compared constantly to that of [[Cher Lloyd]]<ref name=dailymailshane/> and [[Lily Allen]].<ref name=muchmusic/> She has been compared to [[Miley Cyrus]], who also started on the [[Disney Channel]], but in an interview to ''[[Christian Post]]'' Mendler said: \"I'm not Miley Cyrus. There may be some similarities but I'm my own person.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://global.christianpost.com/news/bridgit-mendler-im-not-miley-cyrus-says-rising-disney-star-102905/|title=Bridgit Mendler: 'I'm Not Miley Cyrus' Says Rising Disney Star|publisher=Christian Post|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902040054/http://global.christianpost.com/news/bridgit-mendler-im-not-miley-cyrus-says-rising-disney-star-102905/|archive-date=September 2, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2013, during an interview with the ''Huffington Post'', Mendler was compared to other young artists and asked if she would follow the footsteps in [[pop music]]. Mendler said that \"They've done so much and they're so talented. I think it's tricky because they've been obviously very successful, but I think you always want to be your own person and not be categorized by doing the same thing\".<ref name=huffington/>\n\n==Product endorsements==\nIn 2012, Mendler signed with [[Target Corporation]] to release an exclusive line of clothing inspired by her character [[Teddy Duncan]] of [[Good Luck Charlie]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2011/03/20/target-d-signed-teddy-duncan-collection/|title=Target D-Signed Teddy Duncan Collection|publisher=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219043132/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2011/03/20/target-d-signed-teddy-duncan-collection/|archive-date=December 19, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The ''D-Signed by Teddy Duncan'' fashion collection includes clothing, accessories, hats, scarves, and souvenirs for girls in range from 4\u201318 years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.childmode.com/2011/04/28/disneys-d-signed-teddy-duncan-clothing-collection-hits-stores/|title=Disney's D-Signed Teddy Duncan Clothing Collection Hits Stores|work=Child Mode|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2013, a Spring edition was also released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.girlslife.com/post/2011/03/30/Dress-like-Teddy-Duncan.aspx?cp=all|title=Dress like Teddy Duncan|publisher=Girls Life Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> While promoting her debut single \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", Mendler signed with The Hunt, a [[mobile app]] which combines clothes and shows fashion tendencies.<ref name=thehunt>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehunt.com/the-hunt/rt3NfU-bridgit-mendler's-outfit-in-ready-or-not|title=BRidgit Mendler's Outfit In Ready Or Not|publisher=The Hunt|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> She released exclusively her music video and registered some personal clothes and fashion searches.<ref name=thehunt/> She also had her own version in the games FanFUN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com.br/FanFUN-Bridgit-Mendler/dp/B00M5SSWLY|title=FanFUN: Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> FANfinity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://apps.microsoft.com/windows/pt-br/app/bridgit-mendler-fanfinity/63ac5f1b-956c-4c5b-8ae2-df196b0fcab0|title=Bridgit Mendler FANfinity|publisher=Microsoft|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> While promoting her debut album ''Hello My Name Is...'', Mendler offered exclusive album promotions through Target.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.target.com/p/hello-my-name-is/-/A-14260595|title=Hello My Name Is...|publisher=Target|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> In 2014 she signed with the line of [[dermatology]] products [[Clean & Clear]] and recorded several commercials and campaigns for real beauty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teeninfonet.com/2014/05/31/see-the-real-bridgit-mendler-in-her-clean-clear/|title=See The Real Bridgit Mendler In Her Own 'Clean & Clear' Video!|publisher = Teen Infonet|accessdate = July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[The Legend of Buddha]]''\n| Lucy\n| Voice role\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Alice Upside Down]]''\n| Pamela Jones\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[The Clique (film)|The Clique]]''\n| Kristen Gregory\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]''\n| Becca Kingston\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Labor Pains]]''\n| Emma Clayhill\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Beverly Hills Chihuahua 2]]''\n| Appoline\n| Voice role\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The Secret World of Arrietty]]''\n| Arrietty\n| Voice role (English dub)<ref name=\"Arrietty\" />\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Muppets Most Wanted]]''\n| Minnie\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Lennon or McCartney]]''\n| Herself\n| Documentary<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.majic100.com/blogs/2014/12/17/lennon-or-mccartney|title=Lennon or McCartney?|publisher=Majic 100.3 Fm|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Father of the Year (film)|Father of the Year]]''\n| Meredith\n| originally titled ''Who Do You Think Would Win?''<ref name=whodoy/>\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[General Hospital]]''\n| Lulu's dream daughter\n| Episode dated September 11, 2006\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Jonas (TV series)|Jonas]]''\n| Penny\n| Episode: \"Wrong Song\"\n|-\n| 2009\u20132012\n| ''[[Wizards of Waverly Place]]''\n| [[Juliet van Heusen]]\n| Recurring role (seasons [[Wizards of Waverly Place (season 2)|2]]\u2013[[Wizards of Waverly Place (season 4)|4]]); 10 episodes\n|-\n| 2010\u20132014\n| ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]''\n| [[Teddy Duncan]]\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Lemonade Mouth (film)|Lemonade Mouth]]''\n| Olivia White\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Disney's Friends for Change Games]]''\n| Herself / Contestant\n| 5 episodes, part of Yellow Team\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[So Random!]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Bridgit Mendler, Adam Hicks and Hayley Kiyoko\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[PrankStars]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Secret Agent\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Extreme Makeover: Home Edition]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Walker Family\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Good Luck Charlie, It's Christmas!]]''\n| [[Teddy Duncan]]\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[House (TV series)|House]]''\n| Callie Rogers\n| Episode: \"[[Runaways (House)|Runaways]]\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Austin Mahone Takeover]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Jingle Ball with Sean Kingston & Enrique Iglesias\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Violetta (TV series)|Violetta]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"A Celebrity, a Song\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[We Day]]''\n| Host\n| Television special ([[We Day#Television events|7th edition]])\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Jessie (2011 TV series)|Jessie]]''\n| Teddy Duncan\n| Episode: \"Good Luck Jessie: NYC Christmas\"\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n| ''[[Undateable]]''\n| Candace\n| Main role (seasons [[List of Undateable episodes#Season 2 (2015)|2]]\u2013[[List of Undateable episodes#Season 3 (2015\u201316)|3]])\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Nashville (2012 TV series)|Nashville]]''\n| Ashley Willerman\n| Episode: \"Let's Put It Back Together Again\"\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Merry Happy Whatever]]''\n| Emmy Quinn\n| Main role\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Bone: The Great Cow Race]]''\n| Thorn\n| Voice role\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Bridgit Mendler discography|List of songs recorded by Bridgit Mendler}}\n\n;Studio albums\n* ''[[Hello My Name Is...]]'' (2012)\n\n;Extended plays\n* ''[[Live in London (Bridgit Mendler EP)|Live in London]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[Nemesis (EP)|Nemesis]]'' (2016)\n\n==Concert tours==\n{{Main|List of Bridgit Mendler concert tours}}\n*[[Bridgit Mendler: Live in Concert|Live in Concert]] (2012)\n*[[Summer Tour (Bridgit Mendler)|Summer Tour]] (2013\u20132014)\n*[[Nemesis (EP)#Tour|Nemesis Tour]] (2016\u20132017)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n*[[List of awards and nominations received by Bridgit Mendler]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bridgit Mendler}}\n*{{official website|bridgitmendler.me}}\n*{{IMDb name|1847099}}\n\n{{Bridgit Mendler}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mendler, Bridgit}}\n[[Category:Bridgit Mendler| ]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child singers]]\n[[Category:American female pop singers]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American mezzo-sopranos]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records artists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singers from Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Singers with a three-octave vocal range]]\n[[Category:Songwriters from Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:University of Southern California alumni]]\n[[Category:Walt Disney Records artists]]\n[[Category:Massachusetts Institute of Technology fellows]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actress, singer, and songwriter}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Bridgit Mendler\n| image         = Bridgit Mendler 2013 (Straighten Crop).jpg\n| caption       = Mendler in May 2013\n| birth_name    = Bridgit Claire Mendler\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1992|12|18}}\n| birth_place   = [[Washington, D.C.]], U.S.\n| home_town     = [[Mill Valley, California]], U.S.\n| occupation    = {{flatlist|\n* Actress\n* singer\n* songwriter\n}}\n| years_active  = 2004\u2013present\n| alma_mater    = [[University of Southern California]]<br />[[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]<br />[[Harvard Law School|Harvard University]]\n| relatives     = [[Christine Blasey Ford]] (aunt)<ref name=aunt/>\n| spouse     = {{marriage|Griffin Cleverly|2019}}\n| module        = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background    = solo_singer\n| instrument    = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* guitar<ref name=mcall/>\n* keyboards<ref name=futumbra/>\n}}\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]\n* [[reggae fusion]]\n}}\n| label         = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]]\n* Black Box<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.blackbox.la/|title = Home - Black Box|access-date = November 28, 2016|work = Black Box LA|quote = Mendler is listed under 'Our Clients', where a list of artists signed to their label are listed}}</ref>\n}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Bridgit Claire Mendler''' (born December 18, 1992<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |title=Bridgit Mendler |work=Disney Channel |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029195726/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |archivedate=October 29, 2013}}</ref>) is an American actress, singer, and songwriter.<ref name=\"Bridgit Mendler Bio allmusic\">{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/bridgit-mendler-mn0002397780|title=Bridgit Mendler Bio|first=Matt|last=Collar|publisher=[[AllMusic]]}}</ref> In 2004, she began her career in the animated Indian film ''[[The Legend of Buddha]]'', later starring in the films ''[[Alice Upside Down]]'' (2007), ''[[The Clique (film)|The Clique]]'' (2008), ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]'' (2009)  and ''[[Labor Pains]]'' (2009) as a teenager. In 2009, Mendler signed with [[Disney Channel]] and played [[List of Wizards of Waverly Place characters#Juliet van Heusen|Juliet van Heusen]] on ''[[Wizards of Waverly Place]]''. Following the positive reception to her character, she landed the role of [[Teddy Duncan]] on the Disney series ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'', which ran from April 2010 to February 2014. Mendler also starred in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Lemonade Mouth (film)|Lemonade Mouth]]'' in 2011. Subsequently, Mendler portrayed Candace in the [[NBC]] [[sitcom]] ''[[Undateable]]'' (2015\u20132016) and Ashley Willerman in the musical television series ''[[Nashville (2012 TV series)|Nashville]]'' (2017).\n\nMendler was featured on two singles released from the soundtrack of ''Lemonade Mouth'', with both charting on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. In 2012, Mendler released her debut studio album ''[[Hello My Name Is...]]''.<ref name=\"Billboard\"/> It went on to peak at number 30 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], with over 200,000 copies sold. The record spawned the [[lead single]] \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\" (2012), which was [[List of music recording certifications|certified]] Gold and Platinum in various countries. The follow-up single \"[[Hurricane (Bridgit Mendler song)|Hurricane]]\" (2013) did not achieve the same success. Mendler has links with several philanthropic projects and humanitarian causes. From 2010\u20132012, she served as ambassador to [[First Book]], a campaign to encourage reading and gives books to children in need, and ''Give With Target'', with [[Target Corporation]] to raise funds to reform schools in the United States.\n\n==Early life==\nMendler was born in [[Washington, D.C.]]. She is the daughter of Sandra Ford-Mendler and Charles Mendler, and she has a younger brother named Nicholas.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kidzworld.com/article/25656-adam-hicks-and-bridgit-mendler-qanda# |title=Adam Hicks and Bridgit Mendler Q&A |publisher=Kidzworld.com |date=May 17, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> She moved with her family to [[Mill Valley, California]] at the age of eight.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sing365.com/music/lyric.nsf/Bridgit-Mendler-Biography/1A4C0D3D509D38A84825783100252F15 |title=Bridgit Mendler Biography |publisher=Sing365.com |date=December 18, 1992 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120804000552/http://www.sing365.com/music/lyric.nsf/Bridgit-Mendler-Biography/1A4C0D3D509D38A84825783100252F15 |archivedate=August 4, 2012  }}</ref> It was there where she first expressed interest in acting and began working in plays.<ref name=\"hr\">{{cite web|url=http://www.backstage.com/bso/news-and-features-features/a-star-is-born-1004031788.story?pn=2 |title=A star is born|work=backstage.com|accessdate=December 15, 2010}}</ref> When she was eight years old, Mendler began taking part in local roles in both dramatic and musical theatre, and became the youngest performer in the [[San Francisco Fringe Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |title=Bridgit Mendler \"Teddy Duncan\" |work=Disney Channel |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928175856/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900044&type=mendler |archivedate=September 28, 2013 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> When she was 11 years old, she hired an agent to help her get acting jobs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kiss951.cbslocal.com/2012/06/01/10-interesting-facts-about-disneys-bridgit-mendler/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130119064009/http://kiss951.cbslocal.com/2012/06/01/10-interesting-facts-about-disneys-bridgit-mendler/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=January 19, 2013 |title=10 Interesting Facts About Disney's Bridgit Mendler \u00ab Kiss 95.1 \u2013 Charlotte's #1 Hit Music Station |publisher=Kiss951.cbslocal.com |date=June 1, 2012 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 }}</ref> Mendler is the niece of psychologist [[Christine Blasey Ford]].<ref name=aunt>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/09/20/politics/blasey-ford-family-statement/index.html|title=Ford's family issues statement of support|last=Cole|first=Devan|date=September 20, 2018|work=CNN|access-date=September 21, 2018|others=Contributions by Eli Watkins, Gloria Borger, and Kate Sullivan |quote=In the statement, which was posted to Twitter by Bridgit Mendler, who identified herself as Ford's niece, the family asks that Ford's decision to come forward \"be treated seriously and respectfully\" and that her and her family's privacy be respected as her allegations are investigated. Mendler is an American actress and singer, and starred on a Disney Channel show}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===2004\u20132008: Career beginnings===\n[[File:Mendler 2007.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Mendler at ''[[Alice Upside Down]]'' premiere in 2007]]\nIn 2004, Mendler got her first acting role in the animated [[Cinema of India|Indian]] film ''[[The Legend of Buddha]]'', in which she portrayed Lucy. When she was 13 years old, she got an acting role as a guest star on the soap opera ''[[General Hospital]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author=TV.com |url=http://www.tv.com/people/bridgit-mendler/ |title=Bridgit Mendler |publisher=TV.com |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> She portrayed the dream child of character [[Lulu Spencer]], in which the two have an argument on Mendler's character's birthday.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ducksters.com/biography/bridgit_mendler.php |title=Bridgit Mendler: Actress |publisher=Ducksters.com |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> The scene, lasting just under a minute, is later revealed to be a dream.<ref>{{cite web|author=Fanpop, Inc. |url=http://www.fanpop.com/clubs/bridgit-mendler/videos/8952659/title/bridgit-on-general-hospital |title=Bridgit on General Hospital \u2013 Bridgit Mendler video |publisher=Fanpop |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> That same year, Mendler was the voice of the character Thorn in the video game ''Bone: The Great Cow Race'', which was based on the [[Bone (comics)|Bone comic series]]. In 2007, Mendler made her film debut in the [[film adaption]] of the [[Alice series|''Alice'' series]], titled ''[[Alice Upside Down]]''. Mendler starred alongside [[Disney Channel]] actress [[Alyson Stoner]] and [[Lucas Grabeel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/s?ie=UTF8&keywords=Alice%20Upside%20Down&page=1&rh=i%3Advd%2Ck%3AAlice%20Upside%20Down%2Cp_lbr_actors_browse-bin%3ABridgit%20Mendler |title=Alice Upside Down \u2013 Bridgit Mendler: Movies & TV |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> Mendler portrayed the antagonistic role of Pamela,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotflick.net/movies/2008_Alice_Upside_Down/bridgit_mendler.html |title=Bridgit Mendler in Alice Upside Down |publisher=Hotflick.net |date=May 12, 2007 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> who is the rival of Stoner's character, Alice.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/alice_upside_down/ |title=Alice Upside Down |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/movie/alice-upside-down/id373694290 |title=iTunes \u2013 Movies \u2013 Alice Upside Down |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> For the film's soundtrack, Mendler provided backing vocals on the song \"Free Spirit\", performed by Stoner.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Alice-Upside-Down-Soundtrack/dp/B001FX9Y9Y |title=Alice Upside Down Soundtrack: Various Artists: MP3 Downloads |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> Also in 2007 Mendler auditioned for ''[[Sonny with a Chance]]'' for the role of Sonny Munroe, but [[Demi Lovato]] was chosen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://voices.yahoo.com/lemonade-mouth-star-bridgit-mendler-8322669.html?cat=40|title=Lemonade Mouth Star: Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Yahoo!|accessdate=December 14, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925105138/http://voices.yahoo.com/lemonade-mouth-star-bridgit-mendler-8322669.html?cat=40|archivedate=September 25, 2013}}</ref> In 2008, it was announced that Mendler would play the role of Kristen Gregory in the [[film adaption]] of the popular teen novel series ''[[The Clique (novel)|The Clique]] ''by Lisi Harrison. Mendler had the role of Kristen, a girl who attends OCD on a scholarship, and works hard to keep her good grades.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/s?ie=UTF8&keywords=The%20Clique%2C%20Michael%20Lembeck&page=1&rh=i%3Advd%2Ck%3AThe%20Clique\\c%20Michael%20Lembeck%2Cp_lbr_actors_browse-bin%3ABridgit%20Mendler |title=The Clique, Michael Lembeck&nbsp;\u2014 Bridgit Mendler: Movies & TV |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n\nShe also had begun working on a film with actress and singer [[Lindsay Lohan]] titled ''[[Labor Pains]]'', which kept being pushed back due to various conflicts and problems. Though initially slated for a theatrical release, the film did not receive one in the US and was instead released as a TV film on [[ABC Family]] in 2009. The film did, however, receive a theatrical release in countries such as Russia, Romania, Spain, the United Arab Emirates, Ecuador, and Mexico. The film drew 2.1 million viewers, a better-than-average prime-time audience for ABC Family, and per the network, was the week's top [[Cable television|cable]] film among coveted female demographic groups.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblo/b135139_did_lindsay_lohan_movie_bomb.html|title=Lindsay Lohan new movie|publisher=E! Online|date=December 18, 1992 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> She had a supporting role in the film ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shineon-media.com/2010/03/09/exclusive-bridgit-mendler-interview-disneymania-7-good-luck-charlie-more/ |title=Exclusive Bridgit Mendler Interview: DisneyMania 7, Good Luck Marly & More |publisher=Shine On Media |date= |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132012: ''Good Luck Charlie'' and ''Lemonade Mouth''===\n[[File:Jason Dolley, Bridgit Mendler and Bradley Steven Perry 2010 (cropped)-2.jpg|thumb|left|[[Jason Dolley]], Mendler, and [[Bradley Steven Perry]] in October 2010]]\nIn 2009, Mendler became a recurring character in the [[Disney Channel]] series ''[[Wizards of Waverly Place]]''. Mendler portrayed the role of Juliet Van Heusen,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bridgitmendlermusic.com/releases/wizards_of_waverly_place |title=Bridgit Mendler |publisher=Bridgitmendlermusic.com |date=March 21, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130118122606/http://www.bridgitmendlermusic.com/releases/wizards_of_waverly_place |archivedate=January 18, 2013  }}</ref> a vampire who later forms a romance with [[David Henrie]]'s character Justin Russo. This lasts till the series finale.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/wizards-of-waverly-place/bridgit-mendler-bites-back-on-30041.aspx |title=Bridgit Mendler Bites Back on 'Wizards of Waverly Place' |publisher=Buddytv.com |date=July 15, 2009 |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925165730/http://www.buddytv.com/articles/wizards-of-waverly-place/bridgit-mendler-bites-back-on-30041.aspx |archive-date=September 25, 2013 |url-status=dead  }}</ref> Mendler would go on to appear in eleven episodes total for the series, spanning from 2009 to 2012 when the series ended.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://teenstarfanclub.com/index.php?title=Bridgit_Mendler |title=Bridgit Mendler |publisher=Teen Star Fan Club |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926045958/http://teenstarfanclub.com/index.php?title=Bridgit_Mendler |archivedate=September 26, 2013  }}</ref> In 2010, Mendler became the star of the [[Disney Channel Original Series]] ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'', centering on a teenage girl who makes videos for her baby sister to watch as she gets older.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-eyes-teen-star-86502|title=Disney eyes another teen star|last=Bond|first=Paul|date=July 14, 2009|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=April 7, 2010}}{{subscription required}}<br />{{cite web|url=http://www.dapsmagic.com/disneynewsarticle.php?id=9942|title=Disney eyes another teen star|last=Bond|first=Paul|date=July 15, 2009|work=dapsmagic.com|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63627AIRs?url=http://www.dapsmagic.com/disneynewsarticle.php?id=9942|archivedate=November 10, 2011|url-status=dead}}<sup>'''(Copy of original)'''</sup></ref> The series premiered on April 4, 2010, and was met with a positive critical reception and viewership.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.variety.com/article/VR1118017313.html?categoryId=14&cs=1|title='Idol,' Fox top week in demos|last=Kissell|first=Rick|date=April 7, 2010|work=Variety |accessdate=April 15, 2010}}</ref> In the third season, Disney Channel announced that the series would feature a same-sex couple. This decision caused a protest from the conservative group \"[[American Family Association#One Million Moms/One Million Dads project|One Million Moms]]\" asking Disney Channel not to air the episode. One of Disney's spokespersons told TV Guide the episode was \"developed to be relevant to kids and families around the world and to reflect themes of diversity and inclusiveness.\" Disney aired the episode as planned. Other people including actors [[Miley Cyrus]] and [[Evan Rachel Wood]] expressed their support.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/03/one-million-moms-good-luck-charlie_n_4717515.html |title=One Million Moms Responds To Lesbian Couple On Disney Channel's 'Good Luck Charlie' |first=James |last=Nichols |date=February 3, 2014 |accessdate=June 5, 2014 |publisher=The Huffington Post}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, she starred as Olivia White, the lead role in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Lemonade Mouth (film)|Lemonade Mouth]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/assets/pr%5Chtml/lemonademouth_011811.html |title=Lemonade Mouth |work=Disney Channel |accessdate=December 14, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170917170722/https://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/assets/pr/html/lemonademouth_011811.html |archivedate=September 17, 2017  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wesely |first=Tommy |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/blog/teen-vogue-daily/2011/04/meet-the-girls-of-lemonade-mouth-bridgit-mendler.html |title=Meet The Girls of Lemonade Mouth: Bridgit Mendler: Teen Vogue Daily |publisher=TeenVogue.com |date=April 15, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> watched by 5.7 million viewers on its premiere night.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2011/04/18/friday-cable-ratings-historys-american-restoration-leads-demo-disneys-lemonade-mouth-tops-viewing-sanctuary-smackdown-and-more/89850|title=Friday Cable Ratings: History's ''American Restoration'' Leads Demo; Disney's ''Lemonade Mouth'' Tops Viewing + ''Sanctuary'', ''Smackdown'' and More|publisher=tvbythenumbers.com|date=April 15, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> Mendler performed numerous songs for the film's soundtrack, which was released on April 12, 2011 by [[Walt Disney Records]]. The first single released from the soundtrack, titled \"[[Somebody (Bridgit Mendler song)|Somebody]]\",<ref>{{cite web|last=Gallo |first=Phil |url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/record-labels/bridgit-mendler-signs-with-hollywood-records-1005106532.story# |title=Bridgit Mendler Signs with Hollywood Records |publisher=Billboard.biz |date=March 31, 2011 |accessdate=December 14, 2012}}</ref> was released on March 4, and peaked at number 89 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart.<ref name=\"billboard1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/297431/bridgit+mendler/chart?f=379 |title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=July 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/297431/bridgit+mendler/chart?f=887 |title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Chart history |publisher=Billboard |date= |accessdate=July 29, 2014}}</ref> The second single, \"[[Determinate (song)|Determinate]]\", charted in numerous other countries and peaked at number 51 on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100.<ref name=\"billboard1\"/> In an interview with Kidzworld Media, Mendler confirmed that there will not be a sequel to ''Lemonade Mouth'', commenting: \"There\u2019s not [going to be a sequel to ''Lemonade Mouth''] unfortunately. We had such a great experience working on the movie, and they tried to figure something out for a sequel, but everyone at Disney felt like the movie had completed its story in the first movie. It was a great experience, and I loved working with the cast members and still see them frequently.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsckids.com/2012/05/bridget-mendler-lemonade-mouth-wont-make-a-sequel/ |title=Bridget Mendler \u2013 Lemonade Mouth Won't Make A Sequel |publisher=Bsckids.com |date=May 16, 2012 |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> In 2011, Mendler had the supporting role of Appoline in the straight to DVD film ''[[Beverly Hills Chihuahua 2]]''. Mendler recorded the song \"[[This Is My Paradise]]\" for the film, which was released as a promotional single on January 11, 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/this-is-my-paradise-single/id409885695|title=This is My Paradise \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler|publisher=iTunes|date=February 7, 2012|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref> with a music video directed by Alex Zamm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/20/bridgit-mendler-this-is-my-paradise-music-video/|title=Bridgit Mendler \"This Is My Paradise\" Music Video|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=February 7, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111009121630/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/20/bridgit-mendler-this-is-my-paradise-music-video/|archive-date=October 9, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nOn March 31, 2011, it was confirmed that Mendler had signed with [[Hollywood Records]], and had begun working on her debut album.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/industry/record-labels/bridgit-mendler-signs-with-hollywood-records-1005106532.story#|title=Bridgit Mendler Signs with Hollywood Records|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.teen.com/bridgit-mendler-arrietty-video-interview/ |title=Bridgit Mendler Secret World of Arrietty Video Interview |website=Teen.com |date=February 17, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301222323/http://www.teen.com/bridgit-mendler-arrietty-video-interview/ |archive-date=March 1, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Also in 2011 Mendler also starred the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Good Luck Charlie, It's Christmas!]]'', which premiered on December 2, 2011.<ref name=premiere>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2011/GLC_DCOM_premiere_date.doc|title=\"Good Luck Charlie, It's Christmas!,\" A Disney Channel Original Movie Premieres Friday, December 2|format=[[Microsoft Word|DOC]]|author=Ashley Kline|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|date=October 24, 2011|accessdate=October 25, 2011}}</ref> The song \"[[I'm Gonna Run to You]]\" was co-written and performed by Mendler, and was also featured in the film and released as promotional single on November 12, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/im-gonna-run-to-you-single/id479832434|title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 I'm Gonna Run to You \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler|publisher=iTunes|date=February 7, 2012|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref> Mendler later co-wrote and sang the ''[[Disney's Friends for Change Games]]'' anthem called \"[[We Can Change the World]]\", released as her third promotional single on June 11, 2011.<ref name=\"Disney Channel Medianet\">{{cite web|url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2011/We_can_Change_the_World_release.doc|title=Premiere of Disney's Friends for Change Anthem \"We Can Change The World,\" Performed By Bridgit Mendler, Friday, June 10 on Disney Channel and Radio Disney|accessdate=June 9, 2011|work=Disney Channel|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060009/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/DNR/2011/We_can_Change_the_World_release.doc|archivedate=September 21, 2013}}</ref> In 2012, she guest starred in the television series ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' as Callie Rogers, a homeless runaway teenager with a mysterious illness.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://modoration.com/2012/01/19/sneak-peek-bridgit-mendler-on-house-episode/|title=Sneak Peek: Bridgit Mendler on \"House\" Episode|accessdate=June 9, 2011|website=modoration.com|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120125064243/http://modoration.com/2012/01/19/sneak-peek-bridgit-mendler-on-house-episode/|archivedate=January 25, 2012}}</ref> She also made a guest cameo in Canadian teen drama [[Degrassi: The Next Generation|Degrassi]] in the Season 11 episode \"Don't Panic (1)\" as Clare and Alli's friend Emily Quagmire, in their civics class; she can also be seen in the show's opening sequence sitting on Jake's red truck alongside Alli and Clare. She voiced the lead role of Arrietty in the American English dub of ''[[The Secret World of Arrietty]]'',<ref name=\"Arrietty\">{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-01-08/arriety-u.s-dub-lead-actress-bridgit-mendler-named |title=Arietty U.S. Dub's Lead Actress Bridgit Mendler Named |work=Anime News Network |date=January 8, 2011 |accessdate=March 2, 2011}}</ref> and she recorded a song \"[[The Secret World of Arrietty#Music|Summertime]]\" for the movie which was released as a promotional single on February 2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/summertime-from-secret-world/id499014527|title=Summertime (from \"The Secret World of Arrietty\") \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler|publisher=iTunes|date=February 7, 2012|accessdate=February 7, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132015: ''Hello My Name Is...'' and ''Undateable''===\n[[File:Mendler 043.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Mendler performing on [[Summer Tour (Bridgit Mendler)|Summer Tour]] in July 2013]]\nIn Summer 2012, Mendler confirmed that the title of her official debut single was \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", written by Mendler herself, [[Emanuel Kiriakou|Emanuel \"Eman\" Kiriakou]] and [[E. Kidd Bogart|Evan \"Kidd\" Bogart]]. The song was released for digital download on August 7 and for radio airplay on August 21, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/ready-or-not-single/id548403391|title=Music \u2013 Ready Or Not \u2013 Single by Bridgit Mendler \u2013 iTunes Canada|publisher=iTunes Store (CA). Apple|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref> \"Ready or Not\" peaked at 49 in the United States<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=bridgit mendler|chart=Hot 100}}|title=Billboard Hot 100|publisher=Billboard |date=September 8, 2012 |accessdate=September 13, 2012}}</ref> and 53 in Australia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/35761/chartifacts---wednesday-14th-november-2012|title=Chartifacts \u2013 Wednesday 14th November 2012|publisher=ARIA Charts|date=October 11, 2012|accessdate=September 13, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016010247/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/35761/chartifacts---wednesday-14th-november-2012|archivedate=October 16, 2013}}</ref> but at number seven in the United Kingdom and within the top twenty of the charts in Belgium, the Republic of Ireland and New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/bridget%20mendler/|title=UK Singles Chart \u2013 Bridgit Mendler|publisher=UK Charts|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl//showinterpret.asp?interpret=Bridgit+Mendler|title=Bridgit Mendler Ultratop Discografie|publisher=Ultratop.be/nl/|accessdate=February 25, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/22/2013-03-30/|title=Scottish Singles Chart \u2013 Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Official Charts|accessdate=April 15, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz |title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart &#124; The Official New Zealand Music Chart |publisher=Nztop40.co.nz |date=December 24, 2012 |accessdate=December 28, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2013&year=2013&week=14|title=Discography Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Irish-charts.com. Hung Medien|accessdate=April 24, 2011}}</ref> The song received platinum certification in the United States<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=bridgit+mendler&format=&go=Search&perPage=50|title=US certifications: BridgitMendler|publisher=Recording Industry Association of America|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> and Canada<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?st=Ready+Or+Not&sa=Bridgit+Mendler&smt=0|title=Gold Platinum Database: BridgitMendler|publisher=Music Canada|accessdate=October 17, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203015348/http://www.musiccanada.com/GPSearchResult.aspx?st=Ready+Or+Not&sa=Bridgit+Mendler&smt=0|archive-date=December 3, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> and Gold in Denmark,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.dk/?q=certificeringer&page=39|title=16/05-2013 \u2013 Certificeringer IFPI Denmark|publisher=IFPI Denmark|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> New Zealand<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/|title=Bridgit Mendler on New Zealand|publisher=nztop40.co.nz|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> and Norway.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.no/trofesoknad|title=Bridgit Mendler on Norway|publisher=IFPI|accessdate=October 17, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130324030519/http://ifpi.no/trofesoknad|archivedate=March 24, 2013}}</ref> Mendler ventured on her first headlining tour, [[Bridgit Mendler: Live in Concert]], supporting her first studio album. The tour primarily reached only North America and she played at state fairs, music festivals and Jingle Ball's concerts series.<ref name=wesllfargo>{{cite web|url=http://www.bandsintown.com/event/5818753|title=Bridgit Mendler live in Philadelphia, PA|publisher=Bands In Town|date=October 28, 2012|accessdate=January 1, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060242/http://www.bandsintown.com/event/5818753|archive-date=September 21, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Mendler's debut album, ''[[Hello My Name Is...]]'', was released on October 22 by [[Hollywood Records]] and all the songs were written by Mendler with collaborators, included 12 tracks in standard version and 15 in deluxe edition.<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/480366/exclusive-disneys-bridgit-mendlers-debut-set-for-oct-22 |title=Latest Music News, Band, Artist, Musician & Music Video News |publisher=Billboard.com |date= |accessdate=August 20, 2012}}</ref> Mendler was also involved in its production.<ref name=ft13>{{cite web|url=http://febreteen.com.br/2013/09/bridgit-mendler-fala-sobre-seu-album-atuacao-e-colaboracoes-em-entrevista-confira/|title=Bridgit Mendler at Yapert interview| publisher=Febre Teen|date=August 7, 2012 |accessdate=August 26, 2012}}</ref> The album peaked at number 30 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=bridgit mendler|chart=Billboard 200}}|title=Billboard Chart History: Bridgit Mendler|work=Billboard|date= |accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref> and sold less than 200,000 copies in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vakseen.com/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Soundscan-Week-26-2013.pdf|title=Week 26-2013 SoundScan Chartpack|publisher=Vakseen|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\nInternationally \"Hello My Name Is ..\" debuted in a few countries as Poland, Australia, United Kingdom, France and Spain.<ref>{{cite web | title= Bridgit Mendlerr: Hello My Name Is... \u2013 Album Charts Week November 26, 2012| publisher=ZPAV| url=http://olis.onyx.pl/listy/index.asp?lang=en| accessdate=April 12, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/41701/chartifacts---tuesday-13th-august-2013?pos=7|title=Chartifacts \u2013 Tuesday 13th August 2013|publisher=ARIA Charts|date=October 11, 2012|accessdate=September 13, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060515/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/41701/chartifacts---tuesday-13th-august-2013?pos=7|archive-date=September 21, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://zobbel.de/cluk/130330cluk.txt|title=UK Charts \u2013 Hello My Name Is...|publisher=UK Charts|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Bridgit+Mendler&titel=Hello+My+Name+Is...+Bridgit+Mendler&cat=a|title=Bridgit Mendler discography \u2013 Spain Charts \u2013 Hello My Name Is...|work=Spanish Charts |publisher=Hung Medien |accessdate=December 5, 2009}}</ref> Mendler's vocals have been compared to [[Lily Allen]], [[Cher Lloyd]], [[Jessie J]] and [[Karmin]].<ref name=muchmusic>{{cite web|url=http://blog.muchmusic.com/bridgit-mendler-releases-new-song-hurricane-from-debut-album/|title=Bridgit Mendler releases new song Hurricane from debut album|publisher=Much Music|date=August 7, 2012|accessdate=August 26, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929014009/http://blog.muchmusic.com/bridgit-mendler-releases-new-song-hurricane-from-debut-album/|archivedate=September 29, 2012}}</ref> She released two promotional singles on the album: \"[[Forgot to Laugh]]\" and \"[[Top of the World (Bridgit Mendler song)|Top of the World]]\". On February 12, 2013, her second single, \"[[Hurricane (Bridgit Mendler song)|Hurricane]]\", was released for radio airplay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/cool-new-music|title=Top 40/Mainstream Spotlight Trax|publisher=Top 40 Mainstream|accessdate=September 27, 2012}}</ref> The song peaked at number 1 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Bubbling Under Hot 100 Singles|Bubbling Under Hot 100]] in the United States. On April 2 Mendler released a remix single version<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/hurricane-remix-single/id624664127|title=Hurricane \u2013 Bridgit Mendler (UK)|publisher=iTunes Store (UK). Apple|accessdate=July 9, 2013}}</ref> and, on June 21, an EP remixed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/hurricane-remixes-ep/id661020986|title=Hurricane (Remixes) \u2013 EP \u2013 Bridgit Mendler (UK)|publisher=iTunes Store (UK). Apple|accessdate=July 9, 2013}}</ref> Also in June Mendler debuted her second tour, the [[Summer Tour (Bridgit Mendler)|Summer Tour]], reaching only the United States. In April 30 she released the [[extended play]] ''[[Live in London (Bridgit Mendler EP)|Live in London]]'', by [[Universal Music]], recorded at a special performance in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/live-in-london-mw0002521639|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Live in London|publisher=Allmusic|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.umusic.co.uk/artists/bridgit-mendler/discography/live-in-london|title=Our artists / Bridgit Mendler / Discography / Live In London|publisher=Universal Music|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921061031/http://www.umusic.co.uk/artists/bridgit-mendler/discography/live-in-london|archivedate=September 21, 2013}}</ref> It  on Mendler's [[VEVO]] On November 16, 2013 was premiered the music video for acoustic version of \"[[Top of the World (Bridgit Mendler song)|Top of the World]]\", directed by Matt Wyatt.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vevo.com/watch/bridgit-mendler/top-of-the-world-(acoustic)/USH5V1321961|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 \"Top of the World\" (Acoustic)|work=MTV|date=May 13, 2010|accessdate=May 13, 2010}}</ref>  She recorded it on her own, independent of [[Hollywood Records]], and filmed in [[Griffith Park]], in [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dis411.net/2013/11/16/video-bridgit-mendlers-acoustic-of-top-of-the-world/|title=Video: Bridgit Mendler's Acoustic Of \"Top Of The World\"|publisher=Disney 411|date= |accessdate=March 29, 2013}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Brent Morin, Bill Lawrence, Bridgit Mendler, Rick Glassman from NBC Undateable.jpg|left|thumb|Mendler with the cast of ''[[Undateable]]'']]\nOn June 28, 2014, Mendler began the second leg of her [[Summer Tour (Bridgit Mendler)|Summer Tour]], in [[Charlottetown]], Prince Edward Island, Canada.<ref>{{cite web |first=Doug |last=Gallant |url=http://www.theguardian.pe.ca/Living/Entertainment/2014-04-22/article-3697279/The-Killers-to-play-Charlottetown-July-12/1 |title=The Killers and Bridgit Mendler to play Charlottetown July 12 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=April 22, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304052247/http://www.theguardian.pe.ca/Living/Entertainment/2014-04-22/article-3697279/The-Killers-to-play-Charlottetown-July-12/1 |archive-date=March 4, 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On that date, she sang one of her new songs, \"Fly to You\",<ref>{{cite web |author=[[Tiger Beat]] Staff |url=http://www.bopandtigerbeat.com/2014/06/watch-bridgit-mendler-performs-new-song-fly-to-you/ |title=Watch: Bridgit Mendler Performs New Song, \"Fly to You\" |work=[[Tiger Beat|Bop and Tiger Beat]] |date=June 30, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923193817/http://www.bopandtigerbeat.com/2014/06/watch-bridgit-mendler-performs-new-song-fly-to-you/ |archive-date=September 23, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> about a relationship that was said to be on the rocks but worth fighting for.<ref>{{cite web |author=Nik the Web Chick |url=http://www.q102.com/onair/nik-the-web-chick-26705/bridgit-mendler-debuts-new-song-12515405/ |title=Bridgit Mendler Debuts New Song!! |work=[[WIOQ|Q102 FM]] |date=June 30, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924083434/http://www.q102.com/onair/nik-the-web-chick-26705/bridgit-mendler-debuts-new-song-12515405/ |archive-date=September 24, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On July 5, she performed another new song, \"Deeper Shade Of Us\", with [[disco]] influences.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popline.me/?p=41447 |title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Deeper Shade Of Us |work=Popline |date=July 2014 |accessdate=June 1, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714125649/http://www.popline.me/?p=41447 |archivedate=July 14, 2014 }}</ref> On November 25, 2014, Mendler was announced as a member of the main cast of the [[NBC]] comedy series ''[[Undateable]]'' in season two.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/news/good-luck-charlies-bridgit-mendler-163542451.html |title=Good Luck Charlie's Bridgit Mendler Joins NBC's Undateable as New Regular |work=[[Yahoo!]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205182119/https://tv.yahoo.com/news/good-luck-charlies-bridgit-mendler-163542451.html |archivedate=December 5, 2014 }}</ref> She portrays the character Candace, an unlucky and undefeatably optimistic waitress, who becomes part of the main group.<ref>{{cite web |first=Michael |last=Ausiello |url=https://tvline.com/2014/11/25/bridgit-mendler-undateable-season-2-cast-nbc/|title=''Good Luck Charlie's'' Bridgit Mendler Joins NBC's ''Undateable'' as New Regular |work=[[TVLine]] |date=November 25, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> During the season, Candace and Justin, played by [[Brent Morin]], were dating.<ref>{{cite web |first=Rick |last=Porter  |url=http://www.zap2it.com/blogs/bridgit_mendler_undateable_season_2_secret_disney_weapon-2015-03 |title=Bridgit Mendler is 'Undateable' Season 2's secret Disney Weapon |work=[[Zap 2 It]] |date=March 17, 2015 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Steph |last=Grassullo |url=http://www.teen.com/2015/03/18/celebrities/bridgit-mendler-undateable-interview/ |title=Dating Dos & Don'ts, Plus More Secrets from ''Undateable''{{'}}s Bridgit Mendler |work=[[Teen Magazine]] |date=March 18, 2015|accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> After initial reports, it was confirmed on July 2, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpopular.pe/espectaculos/2015-07-02-bridgit-mendler-ha-sido-eliminada-de-hollywood-records|title=Bridgit Mendler ha sido eliminada de Hollywood Records|website=El Popular|date=July 2, 2015 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> that Mendler left [[Hollywood Records]] earlier in the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.josepvinaixa.com/blog/bridgit-mendler-second-album/|title=Bridgit Mendler second studio album and Leaving Hollywood Records|publisher=Ultimate Music|accessdate=June 23, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150705211527/http://www.josepvinaixa.com/blog/bridgit-mendler-second-album/|archivedate=July 5, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpopular.pe/espectaculos/2015-07-02-bridgit-mendler-ha-sido-eliminada-de-hollywood-records|title=Bridgit Mendler ha sido eliminada de Hollywood Records|publisher=El Popular|accessdate=June 23, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|title=Bridgit Mendler Recording New Album|publisher=The Vinyl Reocord|accessdate=June 23, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706022926/http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|archive-date=July 6, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn early 2015, NBC renewed with Mendler for a third season that consisted entirely of live episodes, which premiered October 15 of that year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/05/08/the-night-shift-renewed-by-nbc-for-third-season/401461/|title='The Night Shift', 'Undateable' Renewed by NBC|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |date=May 8, 2015|accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> In the season Justin proposes to Candace during a [[Backstreet Boys]] show and she accepts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|title=Bridgit Mendler Recording New Album|website=The Vinyl Record|accessdate=June 23, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706022926/http://www.thevinylrecord.com/post/123111284327/bridgit-mendler-recording-new-album|archive-date=July 6, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> On November 13, 2015, minutes before air time, a decision was made to pre-empt the then-upcoming live program due to the [[November 2015 Paris attacks]].<ref>{{cite news |title='Undateable Live' cancels broadcasts due to Paris terror attacks|url=http://zap2it.com/2015/11/undateable-live-cancels-broadcasts-paris-terror-attacks/|accessdate=November 22, 2015|work=[[Zap2It]]|date=November 13, 2015}}</ref> The next week, the live episode references were made about the attack as a tribute.<ref>{{cite news|title='Undateable Live' returns to address Paris attack \u2013 then gets back to funny business|url=http://zap2it.com/2015/11/undateable-live-returns-paris-attack-funny-business/|accessdate=November 22, 2015|work=[[Zap2It]]|date=November 20, 2015}}</ref> Following the third season, it was announced that NBC had cancelled continuation of the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/telenovela-undateable-canceled-nbc-1201755300/|title='Telenovela' & 'Undateable' Canceled By NBC |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Nellie |last=Andreeva |date=May 13, 2016 |accessdate=May 13, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2016\u2013present: ''Nemesis'' and ''Merry Happy Whatever''===\nIn 2016, Mendler produced her second studio album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ryanseacrest.com/2013/08/15/bridgit-mendler-talks-working-on-next-albu/ |title=Bridgit Mendler Talks Working on Her Next Album |website=ryanseacrest.com |date=August 2013 |accessdate=January 1, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140730235103/http://www.ryanseacrest.com/2013/08/15/bridgit-mendler-talks-working-on-next-albu/ |archivedate=July 30, 2014 }}</ref><ref name=billboard2013>{{cite web |first=Gary |last=Graff |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5645350/bridgit-mendler-checks-in-on-touring-hurricane-single-next-album|title=Bridgit Mendler Checks In On Touring, 'Hurricane' Single & Next Album |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=August 9, 2013 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> Mendler discussed some of the producers and songwriters she was working with for the new album, including [[Mitch Allan]], [[Dan Book]], Alexei Misoul, Augie Ray, Beloryze, [[TMS (production team)|TMS]], [[Ina Wroldsen]], and [[Steve Mac]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Daniel |last=Pac\u00f4nio |url=http://febreteen.com.br/2013/11/bridgit-mendler-tera-ajuda-de-tres-compositores-para-novo-album/|title=Bridgit Mendler has help of three composers for new album! |website=Febre Teen |date=November 23, 2013 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Mohammed \"Hamada\" |last=Sherif |url=http://hamadamania.com/2014/02/07/bridgit-mendler-collaborates-with-tms-for-sophomore-album/ |title=Bridgit Mendler collaborates with TMS for sophomore album |website=Hamada Mania Music Blog |date=February 7, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2016}}</ref> On August 4, 2016, Mendler announced the title of her new single, \"[[Atlantis (Bridgit Mendler song)|Atlantis]]\", featuring Kaiydo, which was released on August 26, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/atlantis-feat.-kaiydo-single/id1140618666|title = Atlantis (feat. Kaiydo) - Single by Bridgit Mendler on Apple Music|access-date = August 26, 2016|date = August 26, 2016|work = [[iTunes Store]] (US)}}</ref> The EP, ''[[Nemesis (EP)|Nemesis]]'', was released on November 18.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=Bridgit Mendler|user=BridgitMendler|number=782986855184601089|title=So excited to announce that my #Nemesis EP will be out on November 18th!!! \ud83c\udf89 Pre-order is available right now!!|date=October 3, 2016|accessdate=October 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/nemesis-ep/id1159543311|title=Nemesis \u2013 EP by Bridgit Mendler|work=iTunes Store|location=United States|accessdate=October 3, 2016|quote=Expected Release: Nov 18, 2016}}</ref> In October 2016 Mendler was cast as Ashley Willerman on the fifth season of the CMT television series ''[[Nashville (2012 TV series)|Nashville]]''.<ref name=\"V-Nashville2016\">{{cite web |first=Will|last=Thorne |url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/bridgit-mendler-nashville-season-5-cmt-1201881986/ |title=TV News Roundup: Bridgit Mendler Cast in 'Nashville' Season 5 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=October 7, 2016 |accessdate=October 7, 2016}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"THR-Nashville2016\">{{cite web|first=Kate|last=Stanhope|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/nashville-bridgit-mendler-season-5-936288|title='Nashville' Enlists 'Undateable' Alum Bridgit Mendler for Recurring Role (Exclusive)|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=October 7, 2016|accessdate=March 2, 2017}}</ref> On February 3, 2017, Mendler announced her new single, \"Temperamental Love\" featuring Devont\u00e9e.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2017/02/09/bridgit-mendler-temperamental-love-devonte/ |title=The FADER: Bridgit Mendler Shares The Heart Wrenching \"Temperamental Love\" Featuring Devont\u00e9e|work=The Fader|date=February 10, 2017}}</ref> The music video was featured the Youtuber Jam in The Van.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/bridgitmendler/status/832665399606988800|title=Bridgit Mendler on Twitter|publisher=}}</ref> On February 10, Mendler was cast in lead role of the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] comedy television pilot ''Thin Ice'', created by [[Elizabeth Meriwether]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/bridgit-mendler-star-fox-comedy-new-girl-creator-974632|title=Bridgit Mendler to Star in Fox Comedy From 'New Girl' Creator|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2017/02/10/bridgit-mendler-cast-thin-ice-fox-comedy-pilot-antarctica/|title=Bridgit Mendler to Star in Fox's Antarctica-Set Comedy Pilot Thin Ice|work=[[TVLine]]|accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/thin-ice-cast-bridgit-mendler-isiah-whitlock-fox-1201975948/|title=Bridgit Mendler Lands Lead Role in Fox's 'Thin Ice' Comedy Pilot From Liz Meriwether|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=February 25, 2017}}</ref> but the network ultimately passed on the pilot in May.<ref>{{cite web|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/fox-pilots-dead-linda-from-hr-type-a-thin-ice-behind-enemy-lines-university-1202100550/|title=Fox Update: Network Passes On All Remaining Pilots|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 23, 2017|accessdate=May 25, 2017}}</ref> On August 25, 2017, Mendler released the third single from her upcoming album titled \"[[Diving (Bridgit Mendler song)|Diving]]\" with American group RKCB.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/diving-single/id1266505547|title='Diving' - Single by Bridgit Mendler on Apple Music|work=iTunes|date=August 25, 2017}}</ref> The official music video was released hours after the release of the song.\n\nShe appeared in the [[Netflix]] comedy film ''[[Father of the Year (film)|Father of the Year]]'' along with [[David Spade]], [[Joey Bragg]], [[Matt Shively]] and [[Jackie Sandler]], which was released July 20, 2018.<ref name=whodoy>{{cite web |first=Amanda|last=N'Duka |url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/david-spade-bridgit-mendler-who-do-you-think-would-win-netflix-1202082421/ |title=David Spade, Bridgit Mendler, Nat Faxon, & More Co-Star In 'Who Do You Think Would Win?' For Netflix |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=May 3, 2017 |access-date=May 31, 2017}}</ref>\n\nMendler appears{{when|date=February 2020}} in the eight-part Netflix comedy television series, ''[[Merry Happy Whatever]]'', along with [[Dennis Quaid]], [[Ashley Tisdale]], and her ''Undateable'' co-star [[Brent Morin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/merry-happy-whatever-bridgit-mendler-brent-morin-ashley-tisdale-adam-rose-hayes-macarthur-cast-netflix-series-dennis-quaid-1202580816/|title='Merry Happy Whatever': Bridgit Mendler, Brent Morin, Ashley Tisdale, Adam Rose & Hayes MacArthur Cast In Netflix Series|work=Deadline|accessdate=March 22, 2019|date=March 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\n[[File:Give With Target 0044.png|thumb|right|Mendler visiting a school in [[Baltimore, Maryland]], to donate $25,000 for Target's campaign in 2012]]\nIn 2010, Mendler became ambassador to [[First Book]], a campaign to encourage reading and gives books to children in need.<ref name=\"disneydreaming.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/02/bridgit-mendler-talks-to-radio-disney-about-her-charity/|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks To Radio Disney About Her Charity|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231143026/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2010/12/02/bridgit-mendler-talks-to-radio-disney-about-her-charity/|archive-date=December 31, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2011 it became part of [[Disney's Friends for Change]], a [[Prosocial behavior|pro-social]] \"[[Environmentalism|green]]\" initiative of charity for environmental issues encouraging fans to take action.<ref name=\"disneydreaming.com\"/> As campaign theme that year Mendler released a promotional single on June 11, \"[[We Can Change the World]]\", raising $250,000 for the Disney Worldwide Conservation Fund.<ref name=\"Disney Channel Medianet\"/> She also participated of the [[Disney's Friends for Change Games]], an Olympic-based televised games aired on the [[Disney Channel]], getting $125,000 donation to [[UNICEF]] as Yellow Team captain and also competing for $100,000. But her team lost to the [[World Wide Fund for Nature]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.orlandosentinel.com/disney-a-mom-and-the-mouse/tag/bridgit-mendler/|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130723023657/http://blogs.orlandosentinel.com/disney-a-mom-and-the-mouse/tag/bridgit-mendler/|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 23, 2013|title=Disney Friends for Change Games begin airing June 24 on Disney Channel|accessdate=June 9, 2011|publisher=Orlando Sentinel}}</ref> In 2012 Mendler won the honorary award [[Common Sense Media]] as ''Role Model of the Year'' for her work against bullying.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=http://tv.broadwayworld.com/article/Disney-Star-Bridgit-Mendler-Awarded-2012-Role-Model-of-the-Year-20120426 |title=Disney Star Bridgit Mendler Awarded 2012 'Role Model of the Year' |publisher=Tv.broadwayworld.com |date=April 26, 2012 |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> Mendler was the third young artist to win the award, which usually honors environmentalists and scholars.<ref name=\"common\">{{cite web|url=http://www.commonsensemedia.org/csma2012 |title=Awards \u2013 2012 |publisher=Common Sense Media |date= |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> She also attended the annual [[UNICEF]] acoustic concert in [[New York City|New York]] to raise donations for charity in January 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fanlala.com/news/bridgit-mendler-and-noah-guthrie-added-selena-gomez-unicef-concert|title=Bridgit Mendler and Noah Guthrie Added to Selena Gomez' UNICEF Concert|publisher=Fanlala|accessdate=July 8, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130111010740/http://www.fanlala.com/news/bridgit-mendler-and-noah-guthrie-added-selena-gomez-unicef-concert|archivedate=January 11, 2013}}</ref> In July 2012 Mendler became ambassador of the campaign ''Give With Target'' with [[Target Corporation]] to raise funds to reform schools in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/07/27/bridgit-mendler-give-with-target-campaign/|title=Bridgit Mendler Give With Target Campaign|publisher=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108200253/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2012/07/27/bridgit-mendler-give-with-target-campaign/|archive-date=November 8, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The campaign aims to get $1 billion by 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sweetyhigh.com/blog/karma/bridgit-mendler-joins-target-to-raise-1-billion-for-schools|title=Bridgit Mendler Joins Target to Raise $1 Billion for Schools!|publisher=Sweety High|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> To start the Target campaign, they invested $5 million and distributed $25,000 grants to 100 in-need schools for the school year.<ref name=target2012>{{cite web|url=http://pressroom.target.com/news/target-launches-5-million-campaign-236888|title=Target Launches $5 Million Campaign for Education|publisher=Target|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> Mendler said about the incentive: \u201cI\u2019m excited to partner with Target on their Give With Target campaign and celebrate the start of a new school year with kids across the country. It's so important for all kids to have everything they need for a successful school year\u201d.<ref name=target2012/> In August she got $5 million donated by [[The Walt Disney Company]] and more $2 million donated by people at [[Facebook]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://startingpoint.blogs.cnn.com/2012/08/23/disney-darling-bridgit-mendler-helps-kick-off-nationwide-give-with-target-campaign-for-schools-in-need/|title=Disney darling Bridgit Mendler helps kick off nationwide 'Give with Target' campaign for schools in need|publisher=CNN|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Give With Target 0041.png|thumb|left|Mendler with children-in-need in Baltimore, in 2012]]\nShe was featured in a March 2013 public campaign [[Seventeen (American magazine)|Delete Digital Drama]] with the [[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen Magazine]] to end [[cyberbullying]].<ref name=seventeen2012>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/features/delete-digital-drama-quotes-bridgit-mendler#slide-9 |title=Spread Love, Not Hate|publisher=Seventeen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> About the campaign she said \"Being bullied is something I experienced in school and it is not fun...I love working to end cyberbullying. People don't have to push back as much as they would in real life. People need to realize bullying has just as much of an impact online because words are so cutting and difficult to deal with\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/features/delete-digital-drama-quotes-bridgit-mendler#slide-7|title=Fighting Cyberbullying Comes From The Heart|publisher=Seventeen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/features/delete-digital-drama-quotes-bridgit-mendler#slide-8|title=Bullying Online Is Just As Bad As In Person|publisher=Seventeen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> In May 2013 Mendler traveled to the United Kingdom to fundraise for [[Comic Relief]], given the aim of making her laugh with their jokes for a \u00a31 donation. The campaign aimed to raising \u00a3100,000 and give families hope.<ref name=daily2013>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2293262/Bridgit-Mendler-romance-Good-Luck-Charlie-star-Shane-Harper.html|title=It makes it easier dating another actor... everyone loves us together!' Bridgit Mendler on her romance with Good Luck Charlie co-star Shane Harper|work=Daily Mail|accessdate=May 22, 2013|location=London|first=Sarah|last=Bull|date=March 14, 2013}}</ref> About this work, she said: 'I love supporting something that is so positive and fun for people to get involved in and where people can really do something to help out.\"<ref name=daily2013/> She also worked with [[Acuvue]] being a mentor to help Katie, a winner of the 2013 ''Acuvue 1-Day Contest'', get closer to her dream of making a difference.<ref name=teencharity>{{cite web|url=http://www.teen.com/videos/celebrity-interviews/bridgit-mendler-acuvue-1-day-contest-winner-video/|title=Bridgit Helps Aspiring Singer Reach Her '1-Day' Goal!|work=Teen Magazine|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019053714/http://www.teen.com/videos/celebrity-interviews/bridgit-mendler-acuvue-1-day-contest-winner-video/|archive-date=October 19, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> On October 8 Mendler hosted the event [[We Day]] of [[Free the Children|Free The Children Foundation]], a campaign that helps build schools for underprivileged children of Canadian and American cities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dis411.net/2013/10/08/photos-debby-ryan-bridgit-mendler-and-more-at-we-day-minnesota/|title=Debby Ryan, Bridgit Mendler And More At \"We Day\" Minnesota|work=Disney 411|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weday.com/files/2013/09/FINAL-We-Day-Minnesota-Talent-announcement-Sept-14.pdf|title=Carly Rae Jepsen, Bridgit Mendler and Demi Lovato announced to join headliners the Jonas Brothers and Mia Farrow at We Day Minnesota|work=We Day|accessdate=May 22, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202225728/http://www.weday.com/files/2013/09/FINAL-We-Day-Minnesota-Talent-announcement-Sept-14.pdf|archivedate=December 2, 2013}}</ref> Also for [[Free the Children|Free The Children Foundation]] she was godmother of We Create a Change to help needy children.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2013/10/08/free-the-children-idUSnPNCG93582+1e0+PRN20131008|title=The Jonas Brothers, Carly Rae Jepsen, Bridgit Mendler, Queen Noor of Jordan, Minnesota Vikings and Barbara Pierce Bush take the stage today for We Day Minnesota|work=Reuters|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn November 16, 2013, Mendler participated of the World Challenge Marathon for [[Save the Children|Save the Children Foundation]], a charity race to helps children with health problems.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.savethechildren.org/site/apps/nlnet/content2.aspx?c=8rKLIXMGIpI4E&b=6248025&ct=13371981&notoc=1|title=Bridgit Mendler Takes on Save the Children's World Marathon Challenge|work=Save the Children Foundation|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In March 2014, Mendler traveled to region of [[El Quich\u00e9]], [[Guatemala]] to participate in the other project of [[Save the Children]] that helps underprivileged children in developing countries.<ref name=save1>{{cite news|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/03/31/bridgit-mendler-is-back-home-from-her-save-the-children-trip-to-guatemala/|title=Bridgit Mendler Is Back Home From Her Save The Children Trip To Guatemala|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426215518/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/03/31/bridgit-mendler-is-back-home-from-her-save-the-children-trip-to-guatemala/|archive-date=April 26, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> On April 8, she released the ''Baby Sit In'', that asks for teens to help give parents a break and give babies a healthy start to their life. Mendler said \"It\u2019s an easy way for kids to help little ones everywhere get a healthy start and an opportunity to learn just by doing something they do most weekends anyway\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/04/10/bridgit-mendler-launches-baby-sit-in-campaign-for-save-the-children/|title=Bridgit Mendler Launches Baby Sit In Campaign For Save The Children|work=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426215103/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/04/10/bridgit-mendler-launches-baby-sit-in-campaign-for-save-the-children/|archive-date=April 26, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Mendler represented the institution during the charity congress ''Save the Children's annual Advocacy Summit'' in [[Washington, D.C.]].<ref name=savethechildren>{{cite news|url=http://www.savethechildren.org/site/apps/nlnet/content2.aspx?c=8rKLIXMGIpI4E&b=8943369&ct=13844087|title=Disney Star and Recording Artist Bridgit Mendler and Kids Across America Kick Off Save the Children's #BabySitIn Volunteer Campaign in Nation's Capital|work=Save the Children|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> Carolyn Miles, the Save the Children's president, thanked Mendler publicly for humanitarian work: \"We are thrilled to have Bridgit on board. Her passion for helping children truly came through when she met with families and kids during her visits to the remote communities in the deserts of California and Guatemala's western highlands\".<ref name=savethechildren/>\n\n==Personal life==\n\n===Relationships===\n[[File:Shane Harper PNE 032.png|thumb|right|Mendler performing with her then-boyfriend, [[Shane Harper]], in 2011]]\nOn March 27, 2012, [[Shane Harper]] said in an interview with ''Officially the Hottest'' that he was dating Mendler. Harper told the interviewer that they became friends early in ''[[Good Luck Charlie]]'' and began dating in May 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.m-magazine.com/posts/happy-3-year-anniversary-to-bridgit-mendler-shane-harper-38455|title=Happy 3 Year Anniversary to Bridgit Mendler & Shane Harper!|date=May 20, 2014|work=M Magazine|accessdate=November 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://officiallythehottest.com/exclusive-interview-with-shane-harper/|title=[EXCLUSIVE] Interview With Shane Harper|work=Officially the Hottest|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928010350/http://officiallythehottest.com/exclusive-interview-with-shane-harper|archive-date=September 28, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> In an interview with ''[[Cambio (magazine)|Cambio]]'' in September 2012, Mendler stated that it took two years between her meeting Harper and beginning to date him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambio.com/2012/09/04/bridgit-mendler-and-shane-harper-dating-good-luck-charlie/|title=Bridgit Mendler and Shane Harper Dating: Bridgit Spills All in New Interview|work=Cambio|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In March 2013, Mendler said in an interview with the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' that the fact her boyfriend is also her on-screen boyfriend on ''Good Luck Charlie'' doesn't disturb the relationship: \"I think it makes it easier, especially when it's a person who you've worked with for a long time.\"<ref name=dailymailshane>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2293262/Bridgit-Mendler-romance-Good-Luck-Charlie-star-Shane-Harper.html|title=EXCLUSIVE: 'It makes it easier dating another actor... everyone loves us together!' Bridgit Mendler on her romance with Good Luck Charlie co-star Shane Harper|work=Daily Mail|accessdate=May 22, 2013|location=London|first=Sarah|last=Bull|date=March 14, 2013}}</ref> To ''Classicalite'', Mendler talked about dating Harper, and said it took time for them to begin something, because she needed time to think. She said, \"We knew each other for a while, were friends for a long time. I think everybody was very respectful about it and wanted to make sure that it wouldn't be weird.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.classicalite.com/articles/6293/20140225/bridgit-mendler-talks-dating-shane-harper-good-luck-charlie-finale.htm|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks Dating Shane Harper After 'Good Luck Charlie' Finale and Mia Talerico Death Threats |work=Classicalite|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In November 2015, Mendler revealed that she had ended her relationship with Harper.\n\nIn October 2019, Bridgit announced via her Instagram that she had married her long-term boyfriend Griffin Cleverly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/celebrity-couples/news/a35393/disney-channels-cutest-couple-bridgit-mendler-and-shane-harper-have-broken-up/|title=Disney Channel's Cutest Couple, Bridgit Mendler and Shane Harper, Have Broken Up|author=Noelle Devoe|work=Seventeen|accessdate=November 7, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nMendler has a degree in [[Anthropology]] from the [[University of Southern California]] (USC) in Los Angeles, California.<ref name=degree1/><ref name=degree2/> In 2012 Mendler joined USC's [[anthropology]] class.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://raggedmag.com/school-of-thought-bridgit-mendler-shares-the-perfect-college-curriculum/|title=SCHOOL OF THOUGHT: BRIDGIT MENDLER SHARES THE PERFECT COLLEGE CURRICULUM|work=raggedmag|accessdate=November 14, 2015}}</ref><ref name=hercampus/> She decided to study art after two members of her band joined her at USC.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.recapo.com/live-with-kelly-ripa/live-with-kelly-music/kelly-michael-bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-performance/|title=Kelly & Michael: Bridgit Mendler \"Ready Or Not\" Performance|work=Recapo|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In an interview with Brian Mansfield of ''[[USA Today]]'', Mendler said: \"My plan right now is just to do one class at a time and see how that goes. I'm just going to study something that will be interesting and doable from the road and just take care of my general education courses for now. I want to know something outside of what I do.\"<ref name=usatodayinterview>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2012/11/30/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-on-the-verge/1731703/|title=On the Verge: Disney's Bridgit Mendler|work=USA Today|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> In 2013, she chose anthropology<ref name=universitystar>{{cite web|url=https://star.txstate.edu/node/2231|title=Q&A with Bridgit Mendler, Disney Channel Star|work=University Star|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908073431/http://star.txstate.edu/node/2231|archive-date=September 8, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> and studied [[Medieval art|Medieval Visual Culture]], and medical Anthropology.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/2013/8/27/allentown_fair_bridgit_mendler_hopes_good.htm|title=Allentown Fair: Bridgit Mendler hopes 'Good Luck' follows her through career|work=Hispanic Business|accessdate=May 22, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002064740/http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/2013/8/27/allentown_fair_bridgit_mendler_hopes_good.htm|archivedate=October 2, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seventeen.com/entertainment/reviews/bridgit-mendler-talks-good-luck-charlie-series-finale|title=Power girl bridgit mendler on dealing with change, not knowing what's next|work=Seventeen|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> To the ''[[University Star]]'', Mendler said USC was important so that she doesn't have a formulaic career: \"I think seeing that college life and what that would've been like, it does make you wonder what sort of lifestyle that would be, but I'm really grateful for what I have, and I think it's cool that, because my career path is not as formulaic, I can kind of decide when I want to take time off to do certain things.\"<ref name=universitystar/> In 2016 she graduated as an [[Anthropology|anthropologist]].<ref name=degree1>{{cite web|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/bridgit-mendler-has-found-her-post-disney-voice|title=Bridgit Mendler Has Found Her Post-Disney Voice|work=Noisey|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=degree2>{{cite web|url=http://www.uberhavoc.com/female-disney-stars-all-grown-up-and-smoking-hot/13028/11/|title=18 Female Disney Stars All Grown Up And Smoking Hot|work=Uber Havoc|accessdate=January 17, 2017}}</ref> Mendler has doctorate plans,<ref name=usatoday/> inspired by her mother, doctor of [[public policy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mithun.com/about/leadership/sandy_mendler/|title=Sandy Mendler, AIA, LEED AP|work=Mithun|accessdate=May 22, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141122133016/http://mithun.com/about/leadership/sandy_mendler/|archive-date=November 22, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, Mendler was announced as one of the 2017 [[MIT Media Lab|MIT Media Lab's]] Director's Fellows.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.media.mit.edu/posts/2017-directors-fellows/|title=Media Lab announces 2017 Director's Fellows|accessdate=May 8, 2019}}</ref> In May 2018, she announced on Twitter that she started a graduate program at [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology|MIT]] with a focus on improving social media: \"As an entertainer, for years I struggled with social media because I felt like there was a more loving and human way to connect with fans.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/bridgitmendler/status/991629087197286400|title=First, the reason why I'm taking this time out to study is very connected to how i feel about social media. As an entertainer, for years I struggled with social media because I felt like there was a more loving and human way to connect with fans. That is what I'm going to study|first=Bridgit|last=Mendler|website=Twitter.com|date=May 2, 2018}}</ref> In January 2019, Mendler indicated that she was enrolled in a class at [[Harvard Law School]].<ref>{{cite news |first=Jordyn |last=Tilchen |date=2019-01-25 |df=dmy |title=Congrats: Disney Channel Star Bridgit Mendler Is Headed to Harvard Law School |url=https://www.j-14.com/posts/disney-star-bridgit-mendler-is-going-to-harvard-law-school/|work=J-14|accessdate=April 17, 2019 }}</ref>\n\n===Public image===\nMendler was included [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard's]] \"21 Under 21: Music's Hottest Minors\" list in 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/475070/bridgit-mendler-21-under-21-2012|title=21 Under 21: Music's Hottest Minors 2012|publisher=Billboard|date=February 29, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012}}</ref> In 2013 she also appeared in the list of thirteen.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/5720544/21-under-21-musics-hottest-minors-2013|title=21 Under 21: Music's Hottest Minors 2013|publisher=Billboard|date=February 29, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012}}</ref> She was also chosen as one of the ten hottest young female artists by ''[[Forbes|Forbes Woman]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.womenfitness.net/teenage_celebrities3.htm|title=Forbes Woman \u2013 Fitness Top Ten: Beauty & Fashion: 2012 Top 10 Most Beautiful Female Teenage Celebrities|publisher=Billboard|date=February 29, 2012 |accessdate=March 30, 2012}}</ref> In 2012, Mendler was chosen as role model of the year by [[Common Sense Media]], a non-profit organization that honors innovative minds from the worlds of entertainment, public policy and technology and rewards mainly teachers, scientists and philanthropists.<ref name=\"common\"/> She was honored for her charity work in anti-bullying actions, improving the lives of families by providing a trustworthy role model and creating a positive impact in the world.<ref name=\"auto1\"/> Mendler was the second youngest artist to win the award, after [[Miranda Cosgrove]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rbr.com/miranda-cosgrove-honored-by-common-sense/|title=Miranda Cosgrove honored by Common Sense|publisher=RBR|date=April 26, 2012 |accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\n\n===Influences===\nMendler has cited [[Bob Dylan]] as her biggest musical influence.<ref name=huffington>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/taylor-trudon/bridgit-mendler-on-good-l_b_2867749.html|title=Bridgit Mendler On 'Good Luck Charlie,' Music, And The Craziest Thing A Fan Has Asked Her |publisher=Huffington Postn|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Taylor|last=Trudon}}</ref> To Ed Condran of [[Hartford Courant]] she said that: \"You look at what Bob Dylan and artists like him have done and you just can't help but be blown away. I'm just glad I have the opportunity to start with this and I just want to take it as far as I can\".<ref name=courant>{{cite news|url=http://www.courant.com/entertainment/music/hc-bridgit-mendler-20141029-story.html|title=After A Disney Launch, Bridgit Mendler Making Her Own Sounds|publisher=Hartford Courant|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Taylor|last=Trudon}}</ref> In an interview with [[Disney Channel (Netherlands & Flanders)|Disney Channel Netherlands]], she revealed that her favorite song was \"[[Don't Think Twice, It's All Right]]\" from Dylan's 1963 album ''[[The Freewheelin' Bob Dylan]]''.<ref name=dcNL>{{cite news|url=http://nl.disney.be/disney-channel/backstage/bridgit-mendler/interview#/videoId/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not|title=Bridgit Mendler kwam naar Europa en vertelde over haar muzikale leven|publisher=Disney Channel Netherlands|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Taylor|last=Trudon}}</ref> To Taylor Trudon of ''Huffington Post'' she said: \"He was the first musician I got into where I paid attention to songwriting. He has a way of writing songs that's really playful with lyrics, but at the same time he's saying something that people feel is important and that they relate to. He spoke for a whole generation.\".<ref name=huffington/> Also to Trudon, Mendler cited [[Etta James]], [[Elvis Presley]], [[B. B. King]], [[Lily Allen]], [[Ella Fitzgerald]] and [[Billie Holiday]], and talked about these artists: \"I love that they have soul in their voices. I think that's something important\".<ref name=huffington/> Other musical influences include [[Elvis Costello]],<ref name=DisneyUK>{{cite web|url=http://www.disney.co.uk/disney-channel/features/bridgit-mendler-musical-influences#/videoId/bridgit-mendler-talks-music|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks... Music|work=Disney Channel UK|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[The Delfonics]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a462301/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-single-review.html|title=Bridgit Mendler: 'Ready Or Not' \u2013 Single review|publisher=Digital Spy|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[Red Hot Chili Peppers]]<ref name=asia>{{cite web|url=http://news.asiaone.com/news/showbiz/bridgit-mendler-disneys-feisty-big-sister?page=0%2C1|title=Bridgit Mendler, Disney's feisty big sister|publisher=Asiaone News|date=August 7, 2012 |accessdate=August 26, 2012}}</ref> and [[Van Morrison]].<ref name=newswithtags/> During an interview with [[Yahoo!]], in 2012, Mendler also commented that her first female influence was the [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] girl group [[Salt-N-Pepa]] and sang an impromptu a cappella rendition of the song \"[[Shoop (song)|Shoop]]\".<ref name=yahoo2012>{{cite web|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/the-new-now/disney-actress-and-singer-bridgit-mendler-inspired-by-bob-dylan-and-the-fugees-221919537.html|title=Disney Actress And Singer Bridgit Mendler Inspired By Bob Dylan And The Fugees|publisher=Yahoo|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref>\n\n{{multiple image\n| footer    = Mendler has cited [[Bob Dylan]] (left), [[Florence and the Machine]] (center) and [[Feist (singer)|Feist]] (right) as her musical influences.<ref name=usatoday/>\n\n| image1  = Bob Dylan in November 1963.jpg\n| alt1    =\n| width1  = 110\n\n| image2  = Florence and the Machine-01.jpg\n| alt2    =\n| width2  = 110\n\n| image3  = Leslie Feist performs live at the Showbox in Seattle.jpg\n| alt3    =\n| width3  = 125\n}}\nShe said [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] band [[Fugees]] had great influence in her music training and also the recording of the debut album and song \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", \"One of the writers was like \u2018Check out this Fugees song, \u2018Ready or Not\u2019. So we all listened to it and were like that would be kind of fun to do some sort of interpolation off of that song, which is what we did. I think it stands by itself as its own song but it still has that memorable quality of the Fugees song, which is fun. I think we were all really proud of it and hoping it will go far\".<ref name=popdirt>{{cite web|url=http://popdirt.com/bridgit-mendler-talks-fugees-influence-on-ready-or-not/122712/|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks Fugees Influence On 'Ready Or Not'|publisher=Pop Dirt|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> For her debut album, ''[[Hello My Name Is...]]'', Mendler was inspired by [[indie pop]] singers [[Ingrid Michaelson]] and [[Feist (singer)|Feist]].<ref name=chese>{{cite web |url=http://chestercountymoms.com/2013/08/bridgit-mendler-is-coming-to-the-keswick-theatre-on-august-29-2013.html|title=Bridgit Mendler is coming to the Keswick Theatre on August 29, 2013|date=May 2013 |publisher=Chester Country Moms|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> Among the [[pop music]] artists, she cited [[Maroon 5]],<ref name=grammyinterview/> [[No Doubt]], [[Destiny's Child]],<ref name=newswithtags>{{cite web|url=http://newswithtags.com/Bridgit%20Mendler/artistdirect-bridgit-mendler-talks-hello-my-name-is-summer-tour-and-more#.UdmPH6zW78I|title=Bridgit Mendler Talks \"Hello My Name Is...\", Summer Tour, and More|work=newswithtags.com/|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[Justin Timberlake]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.co.uk/news/bridgit-mendler/377384-bridgit-mendler-one-direction-have-great-voices|title=EXCLUSIVE! We chat to the Disney star about 1D, JT and Britney|work=MTV|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> [[Beyonc\u00e9]] and [[Bruno Mars]].<ref name=huffington/>  She cited [[Jamie Foxx]] as a great model of how to have a career in acting and music.<ref name=huffington/>\n\nMendler said that is influenced by British [[Neo soul|neo-soul]] and listed [[Ellie Goulding]], [[Florence and the Machine]], [[Marina and the Diamonds|Marina Diamandis]], and [[Lianne La Havas]] as her biggest British influences.<ref name=usatoday>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2012/11/30/bridgit-mendler-ready-or-not-on-the-verge/1731703/|title=On the Verge: Disney's Bridgit Mendler|work=USA Today|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|first=Brian|last=Mansfield}}</ref> She has mentioned [[Natasha Bedingfield]],<ref name=newswithtags/> [[Broken Bells]], [[Mark Ronson]] and [[Amy Winehouse]].<ref name=DisneyUK/> In 2013 Mendler revealed to have a big admiration for the [[Adele]]'s musical style. To [[Disney Channel (UK and Ireland)|Disney Channel UK]] she said that \"admire the career of Adele, because she has her own musical style. She does things her way and writes about things she is passionate about. It is really working out well for her\".<ref name=DisneyUK/> She was also influenced by Canadian artists [[Feist (singer)|Feist]]<ref name=grammyinterview>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/news/bridgit-mendler-performs-exclusive-set-at-the-recording-academy|title=Bridgit Mendler Performs Exclusive Set At The Recording Academy|work=Grammy|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref> and [[Tegan and Sara]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dis411.net/2013/02/21/bridgit-mendlers-acoustic-version-of-i-was-a-fool/|title=Bridgit Mendler's Acoustic Version Of \"I Was A Fool\"|publisher=Dis411|accessdate=July 28, 2013}}</ref> To [[Hartford Courant]] she commented: \"I've been a fan of Tegan and Sara's for awhile. They just do what they want to do. They don't follow trends\".<ref name=courant/> She covered the song \"[[I Was a Fool]]\" by the duo and released with the message: \"I heard this song by Tegan and Sara a couple weeks ago and couldn't stop singing it, so I just had to do my own version\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fanpop.com/clubs/bridgit-mendler/videos/34787055/title/bridgit-mendler-fool-acoustic-cover|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 I Was A Fool (Acoustic Cover)|accessdate=July 28, 2013|publisher=Fanpop}}</ref> In 2014, she mentioned in an interview to [[CKQK-FM]] Canadian artists [[Nelly Furtado]], [[Joni Mitchell]] and European bands [[Coldplay]] and [[Little Dragon]] as influences in composing her second album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/hot1055fm/hot-1055-chats-with-bridgit-mendler|title=HOT 105.5 Chats with Bridgit Mendler|work=Hot 105, 5 FM by CKQK-FM|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn acting career, Mendler has cited some influences as [[Jamie Foxx]], [[Natalie Portman]] and [[Rachel McAdams]]. About McAdams she said that \"She plays a variety of roles, she has a lot of charisma, and she doesn\u2019t try to live her life in the public eye\".<ref name=hercampus>{{cite web|url=http://www.hercampus.com/school/george-mason/hc-interviews-bridgit-mendler|title=HC Interviews Bridgit Mendler|work=Her Campus|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref> She also admires the dedication of [[Christian Bale]]: \"I could not live my life as committed to the craft as he does, with body transformations and such, he goes to such extremes but he is very admirable\".<ref name=hercampus/> Mendler also mentioned [[Lindsay Lohan]] as a great actress.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chroniquedisney.fr/dossier/2013-mendler.htm|title=Rencontre avec Bridgit Mendler|work=Chronique Disney|accessdate=May 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Lyrical themes and songwriting===\n{{Quote box|width=30em|align=right|quote=I think the fear when writing a song always that the outside world won\u2019t think it\u2019s as awesome as you do. That\u2019s the scary part about progressing through releasing the song, and also the fun part in sharing it with other people. Sharing that experience with all of these people, it goes from being something that\u2019s very much for me and for the other writers who wrote with me, into being something that\u2019s for everybody else. That\u2019s what performing is. You\u2019re giving it to everyone else. I think that that\u2019s really cool, it\u2019s also super trippy, because you\u2019d never think this thing that you created in a small room with four other people would be something you\u2019d get to share with so many people\".|source=\u2014 Mendler about the writing process.<ref name=popdirt/>}}\n\nThematically, Guilherme Tintel of Portal It Pop has noted that Mendler wasn't immature as the first work of other [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]] artists.<ref name=portalitpop>{{cite web|url=http://www.portalitpop.com/2012/11/review-os-primeiros-passos-de-bridgit.html|title=Review: Os primeiros passos de Bridgit Mendler em \"Hello My Name Is...\"|publisher=Portal It Pop|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> Tintel compares her songs to [[Jessie J]], [[Katy Perry]], [[Natalia Kills]] and [[Taylor Swift]].<ref name=portalitpop/> Mendler said that the writing process isn't hard, because she was influenced by her own experiences.<ref name=popdirt/> Her debut single, \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", talks about self-confidence and deal with boys.<ref name=popdirt/> To Pop Dirt Mendler said: \"I consider myself to be that girl sitting at the curb waiting for the world, so I think it\u2019s a great message to send to just go for the things that you want to take charge of\".<ref name=popdirt/> Her debut album discussed relationships (\"Rocks at My Window\", \"Top of the World\", \"Love Will Tell Us Where to Go\", \"The Fall Song\" and \"Hold On for Dear Love\"), break-up (\"5:15\"), alienation and romantic chaos (\"Hurricane\" and \"Forgot to Laugh\"), self-confidence (\"Ready or Not\"), self-esteem (\"City Lights\"), friendship (\"We're Dancing\"), money (\"All I See Is Gold\") and blonde girls (\"Blonde\").<ref name=portalitpop/>\n\nTo [[Hartford Courant]] she commented that writing is a compulsion. \"It's also something I really enjoy. I like to create. It's part of being a recording artist. I love to write songs\".<ref name=courant/> Mendler also said she didn't want to make [[Mainstream|commercial songs]], but timeless songs. \"I want to make music that stands the test of time. You look at what [[Bob Dylan]] and artists like him have done and you just can't help but be blown away. I'm just glad I have the opportunity to start with this and I just want to take it as far as I can. I wanted variety and to just make things really interesting. This isn't just something that comes out of a machine. It came out of me. This isn't about product. I want to grow as an artist. I remember listening to certain recording artists and songs that had a really big impact on me\".<ref name=courant/>\n\n===Musical and voice style===\nMendler's vocal range spans 3.4 octaves.<ref name=ftvocal>{{cite web|url=http://febreteen.com.br/2013/11/vocal-pop-analise-vocal-bridgit-mendler/|title=VOCAL POP: An\u00e1lise Vocal Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Febre Teen Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref><ref name=vocalpop>{{cite web|url=http://www.vocalpop.com.br/2013/09/analise-vocal-bridgit-mendler_6.html|title=Vocal: Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Vocal Pop Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503215540/http://www.vocalpop.com.br/2013/09/analise-vocal-bridgit-mendler_6.html|archive-date=May 3, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> She's a [[mezzo-soprano]].<ref name=ftvocal/> She plays [[guitar]],<ref name=mcall>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.mcall.com/lehighvalleymusic/2013/08/bridgit-mendler-sees-end-of-disneys-good-luck-charlie-as-opportunity-for-her-music-to-flourish.html|title=Speaking with Bridgit Mendler: Star of Disney's 'Good Luck Charlie' sees show's end as opportunity for her music to flourish|publisher=M.Call|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> [[keyboard instrument|keyboard]],<ref name=futumbra>{{cite web|url=http://futumbra.com/bridgit_mendler/7|title=Bridgit Mendler plays the keyboard while performing \"Song for You\"|publisher=Futumbra|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005003703/http://futumbra.com/bridgit_mendler/7|archive-date=October 5, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> and [[keytar]]<ref name=mmag>{{cite web|url=http://www.m-magazine.com/posts/bridgit-mendler-rocks-out-on-the-keytar-15883|title=BRIDGIT MENDLER ROCKS OUT ON THE KEYTAR!|publisher=M-Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> S\u00e1vio Alves of Febre Teen Magazine said that Mendler's voice was \"strong and sweet\". He calls Mendler's voice as having a \"metallic tone\" and this being \"rare in young female singers\".<ref name=ftvocal/> His voice was compared to [[Indie pop|indie]] and [[blues]] artists.<ref name=vocalpop/> Her music is generally [[Pop music|pop]]<ref name=\"Bridgit Mendler Bio allmusic\"/> and [[reggae fusion]]<ref name=rickey1>{{cite web|url=http://www.rickey.org/bridgit-mendler-r|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 Hello My Name Is\u2026 \u2013 Album Review|publisher=Rickey|date=October 28, 2012|accessdate=January 1, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130415172741/http://www.rickey.org/bridgit-mendler-r|archivedate=April 15, 2013}}</ref><ref name=muchmusic/> and has features of [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]],<ref name=\"Noisey\">{{cite web|url = https://noisey.vice.com/en_us/article/premiere-bridgit-mendler-do-you-miss-me-at-all|title = PREMIERE: Bridgit Mendler - 'Do You Miss Me at All' - Noisey|author = Kim Taylor Bennett|access-date = November 4, 2016|date = November 3, 2016|work = [[Vice (magazine)|Noisey]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Bridgit Mendler Bio allmusic\"/><ref name=\"muchmusic\"/> [[funk]],<ref name=gossiplife>{{cite web|url=http://thismoment.gossipfile.com/2012/09/23/bridgit-mendler-hurricane-listen-now/|title=Bridgit Mendler \u2013 'Hurricane' LISTEN NOW|publisher=Gossip File|date=August 7, 2012|accessdate=August 26, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130216042831/http://thismoment.gossipfile.com/2012/09/23/bridgit-mendler-hurricane-listen-now/|archivedate=February 16, 2013}}</ref> and [[hip hop soul]].<ref name=asia/> In an interview, she said she prefers to escape the traditional [[Pop music|pop]] and [[dance-pop]] and adding other elements. \"I have [[funk]]y, [[R&B]] tendencies when I write by myself. I really love [[doo-wop]] and a [[jazz]]y swing beat. Rhythm is a big emphasis in my own writing\".<ref name=chese/> Her voice and style has been compared constantly to that of [[Cher Lloyd]]<ref name=dailymailshane/> and [[Lily Allen]].<ref name=muchmusic/> She has been compared to [[Miley Cyrus]], who also started on the [[Disney Channel]], but in an interview to ''[[Christian Post]]'' Mendler said: \"I'm not Miley Cyrus. There may be some similarities but I'm my own person.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://global.christianpost.com/news/bridgit-mendler-im-not-miley-cyrus-says-rising-disney-star-102905/|title=Bridgit Mendler: 'I'm Not Miley Cyrus' Says Rising Disney Star|publisher=Christian Post|accessdate=March 31, 2013|date=June 20, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902040054/http://global.christianpost.com/news/bridgit-mendler-im-not-miley-cyrus-says-rising-disney-star-102905/|archive-date=September 2, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2013, during an interview with the ''Huffington Post'', Mendler was compared to other young artists and asked if she would follow the footsteps in [[pop music]]. Mendler said that \"They've done so much and they're so talented. I think it's tricky because they've been obviously very successful, but I think you always want to be your own person and not be categorized by doing the same thing\".<ref name=huffington/>\n\n==Product endorsements==\nIn 2012, Mendler signed with [[Target Corporation]] to release an exclusive line of clothing inspired by her character [[Teddy Duncan]] of [[Good Luck Charlie]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2011/03/20/target-d-signed-teddy-duncan-collection/|title=Target D-Signed Teddy Duncan Collection|publisher=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=July 8, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141219043132/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2011/03/20/target-d-signed-teddy-duncan-collection/|archive-date=December 19, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The ''D-Signed by Teddy Duncan'' fashion collection includes clothing, accessories, hats, scarves, and souvenirs for girls in range from 4\u201318 years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.childmode.com/2011/04/28/disneys-d-signed-teddy-duncan-clothing-collection-hits-stores/|title=Disney's D-Signed Teddy Duncan Clothing Collection Hits Stores|work=Child Mode|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2013, a Spring edition was also released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.girlslife.com/post/2011/03/30/Dress-like-Teddy-Duncan.aspx?cp=all|title=Dress like Teddy Duncan|publisher=Girls Life Magazine|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> While promoting her debut single \"[[Ready or Not (Bridgit Mendler song)|Ready or Not]]\", Mendler signed with The Hunt, a [[mobile app]] which combines clothes and shows fashion tendencies.<ref name=thehunt>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehunt.com/the-hunt/rt3NfU-bridgit-mendler's-outfit-in-ready-or-not|title=BRidgit Mendler's Outfit In Ready Or Not|publisher=The Hunt|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> She released exclusively her music video and registered some personal clothes and fashion searches.<ref name=thehunt/> She also had her own version in the games FanFUN<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com.br/FanFUN-Bridgit-Mendler/dp/B00M5SSWLY|title=FanFUN: Bridgit Mendler|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> FANfinity.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://apps.microsoft.com/windows/pt-br/app/bridgit-mendler-fanfinity/63ac5f1b-956c-4c5b-8ae2-df196b0fcab0|title=Bridgit Mendler FANfinity|publisher=Microsoft|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> While promoting her debut album ''Hello My Name Is...'', Mendler offered exclusive album promotions through Target.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.target.com/p/hello-my-name-is/-/A-14260595|title=Hello My Name Is...|publisher=Target|accessdate=July 8, 2012}}</ref> In 2014 she signed with the line of [[dermatology]] products [[Clean & Clear]] and recorded several commercials and campaigns for real beauty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://teeninfonet.com/2014/05/31/see-the-real-bridgit-mendler-in-her-clean-clear/|title=See The Real Bridgit Mendler In Her Own 'Clean & Clear' Video!|publisher = Teen Infonet|accessdate = July 8, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2004\n| ''[[The Legend of Buddha]]''\n| Lucy\n| Voice role\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2007\n| ''[[Alice Upside Down]]''\n| Pamela Jones\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2008\n| ''[[The Clique (film)|The Clique]]''\n| Kristen Gregory\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | 2009\n| ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Squeakquel]]''\n| Becca Kingston\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | 2009\n| ''[[Labor Pains]]''\n| Emma Clayhill\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2011\n| ''[[Beverly Hills Chihuahua 2]]''\n| Appoline\n| Voice role\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2012\n| ''[[The Secret World of Arrietty]]''\n| Arrietty\n| Voice role (English dub)<ref name=\"Arrietty\" />\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | 2014\n| ''[[Muppets Most Wanted]]''\n| Minnie\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | 2014\n| ''[[Lennon or McCartney]]''\n| Herself\n| Documentary<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.majic100.com/blogs/2014/12/17/lennon-or-mccartney|title=Lennon or McCartney?|publisher=Majic 100.3 Fm|date=May 30, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2018\n| ''[[Father of the Year (film)|Father of the Year]]''\n| Meredith\n| originally titled ''Who Do You Think Would Win?''<ref name=whodoy/>\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2006\n| ''[[General Hospital]]''\n| Lulu's dream daughter\n| Episode dated September 11, 2006\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2009\n| ''[[Jonas (TV series)|Jonas]]''\n| Penny\n| Episode: \"Wrong Song\"\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| 2009\u20132012\n| ''[[Wizards of Waverly Place]]''\n| [[Juliet van Heusen]]\n| Recurring role (seasons [[Wizards of Wav