{"title_page": "Antoine Daniel (YouTuber)", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name                = Antoine Daniel\n| image               = Antoine_Daniel_-_N\u00e9oCast2_-_3_(cropped).jpg\n| caption             = Antoine Daniel in 2016.\n| birth_name          = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1989|4|23|df=yes}}\n| death_place         = \n| nationality         = French\n| alma_mater          = \n| occupation          = \n| website             = \n| pseudonym           = MrAntoineDaniel\n| channel_name        = MrAntoineDaniel\n| years_active        = 2012-2017\n| genre               = Humor\n| subscribers         = 2.7 million\n| subscriber_date     = September 2017\n| views               = 270 million\n| view_date           = September 2017\n}}\n\n'''Antoine Daniel''' is a video maker, editor and French actor born on 23 April 1989.<ref>http://dirigeants.bfmtv.com/Antoine-DANIEL-5499034/</ref> He is known for his famous humoristic program ''What The Cut !?'', published since 1 March 2012 on [[YouTube]].<ref>http://www.konbini.com/fr/tendances-2/konbini-web-rencontre-avec-le-mec-derriere-what-the-cut/</ref> He has become extremely successful reaching more than 2.8 million subscribers in August 2018. Here his a preview of his french \"Peck Room\" https://image.noelshack.com/fichiers/2020/16/6/1587168519-antoine-daniel-portrait.jpg\n\n== Biography ==\nAntoine Daniel studied for two years at the [[\u00c9cole Sup\u00e9rieure de R\u00e9alisation Audiovisuelle|ESRA]] in [[Paris]] before beginning his training in sound engineering while devoting himself to musical composition. Once he acquired his [[Brevet de Technicien Sup\u00e9rieur|BTS]], he was temporarily employed in a musical publishing house as an operator input, an experience which he didn't enjoy. It was during that time, on 1 March 2012, that he created the show ''What The Cut !?''.\n\n==YouTube==\n===''What The Cut !?''===\n''What The Cut !?'' was a humoristic show created by Antoine Daniel, the first episode of \"What The Cut !?\" was uploaded on 1 March 2012 on his YouTube channel. The concept of the show comes from [[Ray William Johnson]]'s ''Equals Three''. When it comes to his humor and staging inspirations, his most obvious references are videographer [[TomSka]] and British director [[Edgar Wright]].\n\nIn each episode of ''What The Cut !?'', Antoine Daniel analyses three funny, strange or freaky videos, and jokingly comments on them. However, ''What The Cut !?'' isn't a French \"Equals Three\" as Antoine Daniel completely changed the concept. In ''What The Cut !?'' he plays a character who speaks very quickly, wildly and sometimes screams. The video editing is very quick and the jokes are completely absurd which explains the show's name : \"What the ...\" for the absurd, wacky and crazy jokes and humor, and \"Cut\", for the video editing, which Antoine Daniel considers the most important part of his videos.\n\n===''Clyde Vanilla''===\n{{Expand section|date=September 2017}}\n''Clyde Vanilla'' is a [[science fiction]] [[Audiobook|audio story]]. The first episode was released on 17 September 2017.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniel, Antoine}}\n[[Category:French YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Internet celebrities]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name                = Antoine Daniel\n| image               = Antoine_Daniel_-_N\u00e9oCast2_-_3_(cropped).jpg\n| caption             = Antoine Daniel in 2016.\n| birth_name          = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1989|4|23|df=yes}}\n| death_place         = \n| nationality         = French\n| alma_mater          = \n| occupation          = \n| website             = \n| pseudonym           = MrAntoineDaniel\n| channel_name        = MrAntoineDaniel\n| years_active        = 2012-2017\n| genre               = Humor\n| subscribers         = 2.7 million\n| subscriber_date     = September 2017\n| views               = 270 million\n| view_date           = September 2017\n}}\n\n'''Antoine Daniel''' is a video maker, editor and French actor born on 23 April 1989.<ref>http://dirigeants.bfmtv.com/Antoine-DANIEL-5499034/</ref> He is known for his famous humoristic program ''What The Cut !?'', published since 1 March 2012 on [[YouTube]].<ref>http://www.konbini.com/fr/tendances-2/konbini-web-rencontre-avec-le-mec-derriere-what-the-cut/</ref> He has become extremely successful reaching more than 2.8 million subscribers in August 2018.\n\n== Biography ==\nAntoine Daniel studied for two years at the [[\u00c9cole Sup\u00e9rieure de R\u00e9alisation Audiovisuelle|ESRA]] in [[Paris]] before beginning his training in sound engineering while devoting himself to musical composition. Once he acquired his [[Brevet de Technicien Sup\u00e9rieur|BTS]], he was temporarily employed in a musical publishing house as an operator input, an experience which he didn't enjoy. It was during that time, on 1 March 2012, that he created the show ''What The Cut !?''.\n\n==YouTube==\n===''What The Cut !?''===\n''What The Cut !?'' was a humoristic show created by Antoine Daniel, the first episode of \"What The Cut !?\" was uploaded on 1 March 2012 on his YouTube channel. The concept of the show comes from [[Ray William Johnson]]'s ''Equals Three''. When it comes to his humor and staging inspirations, his most obvious references are videographer [[TomSka]] and British director [[Edgar Wright]].\n\nIn each episode of ''What The Cut !?'', Antoine Daniel analyses three funny, strange or freaky videos, and jokingly comments on them. However, ''What The Cut !?'' isn't a French \"Equals Three\" as Antoine Daniel completely changed the concept. In ''What The Cut !?'' he plays a character who speaks very quickly, wildly and sometimes screams. The video editing is very quick and the jokes are completely absurd which explains the show's name : \"What the ...\" for the absurd, wacky and crazy jokes and humor, and \"Cut\", for the video editing, which Antoine Daniel considers the most important part of his videos.\n\n===''Clyde Vanilla''===\n{{Expand section|date=September 2017}}\n''Clyde Vanilla'' is a [[science fiction]] [[Audiobook|audio story]]. The first episode was released on 17 September 2017.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniel, Antoine}}\n[[Category:French YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Internet celebrities]]\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "KarimLaMalice", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antoine_Daniel_(YouTuber)"}
{"title_page": "Tom J. Lee", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name=Thomas J. Lee\n| image =\n| imagesize = \n| caption=\n| nationality=\n| office=[[Texas House of Representatives]] District 68\n| term_start=January 12, 1965\n| term_end=January 10, 1967\n| preceded=\n| succeeded=\n| birth_date={{Birth date|1923|9|25}}\n| death_date={{Death date and age|1996|11|7|1923|9|25}}\n| death_place=\n| death_cause=\n| resting_place=\n| birth_place=\n| party= [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]]\n| residence=\n| occupation=\n| spouse= \n| children=\n|alma_mater=\n| footnotes= First [[Asian-American]] to serve in the Texas Legislature\n}}\nThomas J. Lee (September 25, 1923 - November 7, 1996) is an American politician. Lee was the first [[Asian-American]] to serve in the Texas Legislature.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lrl.texas.gov/legeleaders/members/memberdisplay.cfm?memberID=1022/|title=Thomas J. Lee, Legislative Reference Library of Texas}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authoritycontrol}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lee, Tom J}}\n\n\n{{Uncategorized stub|date=April 2020}}\n{{Texas-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "Thomas J. Lee (September 25, 1923 - November 7, 1996) is an American politician. Lee was the first [[Asian-American]] to serve in the Texas Legislature.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lrl.texas.gov/legeleaders/members/memberdisplay.cfm?memberID=1022/|title=Thomas J. Lee, Legislative Reference Library of Texas}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authoritycontrol}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lee, Tom J}}\n\n\n{{Uncategorized stub|date=April 2020}}\n{{Texas-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Evvekk", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added infobox", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_J._Lee"}
